title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Cook and drain sausage.
Place noodles in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour sausage over noodles.
Add green chilies, mushroom soup, evaporated milk and cheese soup. Cover with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with crescent rolls, firmly pressing together to form crust.
Add crumbled sausage and cheese.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Make
crust by mixing graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted butter.
Press in bottom of rectangle pan.

title: stuffed jalapeno peppers
directions: Drain and remove stems from peppers. (Be sure to remove all seeds.) Combine all remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly. Pat mixture into patties 1/4-inch thick. Make patties large enough to wrap around stuffed pepper. Mixture should seal off entire surface of pepper. Deep-fry 4 to 5 minutes in hot oil or until browned. Makes 21.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add flour and mix until crumbly. Add pecans. Reserve about 1 3/4 cups of mixture.
Pour the remaining mixture into a greased 10 x 15 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread preserve evenly over crust. Sprinkle reserved mixture over preserves and bake an additional 25 to 30 minutes.
Let set after removing from oven. Cut into squares while still warm. Makes 3 dozen squares.

title: jello dream dish
directions: Make jello using hot water first; add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add cold water.
Add pineapple and banana to jello. Put in refrigerator to sit.

title: olive-nut spread
directions: Mash the softened cream cheese with a fork.
Blend in the mayonnaise.
Stir in the chopped nuts and olives.
Add the olive juice and the pepper and blend well.
Do not add any salt. Refrigerate several hours to improve consistency.
This is delicious in finger sandwiches, on very thin toast, or on crackers.

title: triplet cookie recipe
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Spoon flour (not sifted) into dry measuring cup.
Level off and pour measured flour onto a square of waxed paper.
Add salt and soda to flour and stir to blend.
Add blended dry ingredients to creamed mixture and mix well.
Divide dough into 3 portions for variations.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut all ingredients very small.
Use only the flowerets of the broccoli and cauliflower.

title: lo-cal cherry-cola salad
directions: Bring cherries in juice to boil in water.
Add gelatin; stir. Cool 30 minutes.
Add cola, celery and pineapple.
Chill until set.
Excellent for diabetics and dieters.
Chopped pecans can be added.

title: cream cheese dream
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Even non-spinach eaters like this one!

title: double quick dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, 1/2 of the flour and salt.
Beat with a spoon until smooth.
Add egg and shortening. Beat in the rest of the flour until smooth.
Cover with a cloth and let rise for 30 minutes.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Stir dough. Put into muffin cups.
Cover and let rise an additional 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate delight cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Beat thoroughly.
Add sifted flour and beat. Add chocolate syrup and blend well with electric mixer for a minute.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Test with toothpick. Do not open oven until cake has cooked at least 15 minutes or cake might fall. Cool slightly before icing.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix coconut, sour cream and sugar and let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.
Cook layers made from cake mix and split those two into 4 pieces or layers and ice.

title: berry cobbler(a.k.a. washday pie)
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Melt oleo in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk; pour into dish of melted oleo.
Do not stir!
Add 1 can of favorite pie filling.
Do not stir! Bake 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except last two together in a buttered dish.
Top with melted butter and corn flakes.
Bake at 320° for 40 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Separate eggs and beat whites until stiff.
Set aside.
Cream margarine and vegetable shortening and add sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add alternately with flour.
Beat well.
Add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into three greased and floured 9-inch cake pans, using 2 cups batter for each pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking pan and cook like brownies at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: french chocolate meringue puffs
directions: Melt chocolate chips over hot water.
Cool for approximately 5 minutes.
Combine egg whites and vanilla extract.
Beat until stiff, but not dry.
Beat in sugar gradually until stiff.
Fold in crackers and melted chocolate.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° preheated oven.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: play dough
directions: Heat salt and alum in water until dissolved.
Mix with flour. Cool and knead.
Divide and add food coloring.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook all ingredients together until done.
If becomes too thick, add more water.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine flour and sugar then add to scalded milk and cook over low heat.
Add some hot mixture to egg then add to mixture. Cook over low heat until thick.
Stir constantly so it will not lump. Stir in vanilla and margarine.
Layer with bananas and vanilla wafers.
Crumble some vanilla wafers on top.

title: vegetarian omelette
directions: Put a little oil in skillet.
Pour in egg substitute and let harden a little.
Combine the rest of the ingredients, except the spaghetti sauce.
Pour into semi-soft eggs.

title: spam and cheese bake
directions: Cook together in skillet Crisco or butter and onion.
Add potato juice, cooked potatoes and milk.
Add flour to thicken. Add Spam.
Add cheese.
Add spices.
Put potatoes in casserole. Add cooked ingredients and top with rest of cheese.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Take one can salmon, flake with a silver fork, removing skin and bones.
Add one egg, salt and pepper, one cup milk and one cup of crumbs.
Form into a loaf.
Pour over tablespoon butter mixed with a little lemon juice and bake one-half hour.

title: terika's tortilla snacks
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and spread on tortillas.
Roll up tortilla and cut into squares.
Enjoy.

title: virginia scanlon's lemon meringue pie supreme
directions: Mix cornstarch, flour, the 1 cup sugar and salt together in saucepan.
Stir in boiling water and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Reduce heat to low and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir a small amount of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Stir well and return to mixture in saucepan.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add butter, lemon juice and lemon rind and stir well. Cool, covered, to room temperature before pouring in pastry shell.

title: stuffed mushrooms(ham and cream cheese)
directions: Wash 8 ounces fresh mushrooms.
Remove and chop stems.
Place stems in small bowl with onion or butter, if included in recipe. Cover with plastic wrap.
Arrange caps on paper towel lined plate with larger caps to outside.
Microwave 1 1/2 to 3 minutes, until heated, rotating plate once or twice.
Microwave at High 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes, until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Mound in mushroom caps.

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: In a large pan, mix cooked hamburger, onions, beans, soup and Ro-Tel. Heat until warm. Spoon mixture into tortillas and roll, stacking in a casserole dish. Cover with remaining mixture. Slice Velveeta and cover top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: excellent party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in cookie pan.
Heat for 45 minutes in 250° oven; stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper towels to cool.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Grind beef in blender until fine.
Save 1/3 for rolling.
Mix beef with cream cheese.
Blend onion until fine in blender or food processor.
Mix with cheese.
Form ball.
Freeze 10 to 20 minutes. Roll in reserved beef.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil brown sugar, white corn syrup, margarine and salt in saucepan for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla.
Stir well over popped corn.
Spread in large roaster. Place in oven for 1 hour at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; press down.
Cool.
Store, covered.

title: white clam sauce spaghetti
directions: Heat margarine and olive oil. Add chopped green onions and saute briefly. Add oregano, basil, garlic, tomato, mushrooms, salt, pepper and clam juice. Simmer briefly. Add clams and keep hot. Boil spaghetti and cook according to package. Drain and return to pan. Add sauce and 4 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.

title: art glass dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix graham crackers, butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 8 minutes.

title: cheese fruit dip
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until softened. Mix all ingredients together on medium speed.
Chill about 30 minutes.
Serve with sliced apples or any of your favorite fruit. Very good.

title: fruit cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add beaten eggs, one at a time.
Stir in sugar. Add 1 1/2 cups flour and baking powder.
In separate bowl, combine fruits, nuts and 1/4 cup flour.
Stir extracts into batter, then add fruit and nuts.
Pour batter into lined tube pan.
Place cake in cold oven.
Turn on to 250°.
Bake for 3 hours.

title: skilletburgers
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off grease.
Stir in onion and celery.
Stir in tomato sauce, soup, hot pepper, salt and chili powder.
Let simmer about 15 minutes.
Split and toast buns, put mixture on top.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package direction; drain.
In skillet, brown meat.
Drain off excess fat.
Add green peppers and seasonings.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, tomato sauce and paste.
Blend together cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream.
Stir in green onions.

title: ruth's cheese ball
directions: Have all cheese at room temperature. Grate the Cheddar cheese and the sharp cheese. Add the soft cream cheese, Blue cheese and the horseradish. Mix well with hands or a big mixer. Roll into large ball. Use wax paper or counter top. Spread pecans (chopped fine) and roll the cheese ball until well covered. Use your thumb and make dent in top of the cheese ball. Put a red cherry in it.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in halves lengthwise.
Remove seeds and wash. Combine hamburger, rice, onions, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Pile lightly into pepper halves and place in large baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce on top of each pepper.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until peppers are tender, basting occasionally.

title: baked beans for 2
directions: Cover Beans with cold water; soak overnight.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until skins burst.
Put Beans in a pot with Seasonings and cooking water (not too much water); Onion in bottom of pot.
Score Salt Pork and put on top of beans.
Cover pot; cook 6 hours at 250.
Remove cover for last hour.

title: turkey pizza
directions: Mix the yeast and warm water.
Add the flour until well blended, then let it rise for 2 to 3 hours.
In a large saucepan, brown the ground turkey, then add the pepper and onion, cooking until the vegetables are tender.
Add the spaghetti sauce mix, tomato paste and water; simmer for 15 minutes.
Divide the dough into thirds and pat to spread into 3 greased pizza pans.
Spread with sauce; sprinkle with shredded low-fat Mozzarella.
Bake in a 400° oven until cheese is lightly browned.

title: lebkuchen
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, fruit and nuts.
Sift together flour and other dry ingredients.
Gradually add dry mixture to the egg mixture, stirring only enough to moisten the flour.
Spread 1/2-inch thick in a greased pan; bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm and drizzle with powdered sugar/water glaze.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes until gold.
Cool.

title: maryland style crab cakes
directions: Carefully pick out all bones in the crabmeat; set aside.
Saute the onion and red and yellow peppers until clear.
Mix the grain mustard, mayonnaise, spices and crabmeat.
Mix and add 1 egg yolk and 1 1/2 cups of plain bread crumbs.
Taking a tablespoon, spoon out level portions of mixture until finished.
Pat them out to 1/2 inch crab cakes.
Use remaining bread crumbs to "bread" the cakes. Saute them in 1/4 inch of olive oil until golden brown on both sides.
Squeeze fresh lemon juice; dip in tartar sauce and enjoy!

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Mix last 3 ingredients and microwave for 3 minutes; stir every minute.
Cool and stir several times while cooling.
Add the first mixture to the second mixture.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix orange Kool-Aid according to package and then add other ingredients.

title: easy chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Save broth.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Saute in skillet butter, onion, celery and bell pepper. Grate cheese.
Drain spaghetti, leaving some broth.
Add soups and tomatoes.
Add onion and celery mixture to spaghetti.
Add grated cheese and stir, adding broth if needed.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir and cook on low for 30 minutes or put in baking dish. Top with cheese and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple custard
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple or lemon-cheese icing
directions: Beat eggs.
Add 1/2 cup of water to eggs.
Set aside.
Combine sugar and flour.
Add 1/2 cup of water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir a small amount of hot mixture in eggs, then add eggs to mixture.
Add butter.
Add lemon juice or pineapple.
Cook until done (about 1 minute).
Place on cake.

title: vanilla wafers
directions: Mix together and drop small spoonfuls on a slightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven 8 minutes until edges are brown. Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: maple overnights
directions: Cream
brown
sugar,
margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and nuts.
Mix together and refrigerate until cold.
Shape
into 2 rolls.
Put in wax paper and freeze.
Slice very thin and bake until brown at 325°.

title: cinnamon raisin cookies
directions: In a small bowl, using a mixer, beat eggs until fluffy.
Set aside.
In another large bowl, cream butter and brown sugar.
When fluffy, gradually add beaten egg, vanilla and water.
In another bowl, sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Pour half of sifted ingredients into creamed mixture.
Stir together. Gradually add rest of batter.
Add cinnamon and raisins.
Place 1 heaping teaspoon 1 1/2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: roast leg of lamb
directions: Sliver garlic and place in small slits in meat.
Cover meat with flour and sprinkle with salt, pepper, basil and garlic powder.
Place on rack in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Start at 425° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes per pound until juices run clear.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: In bowl, put zucchini, beaten eggs, onion, Mozzarella cheese and oil.
Fold in Bisquick and parsley.
Put into greased 9-inch pie or quiche dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Beat eggs. Add milk, pumpkin and butter. Blend dry ingredients.
Mix together.
Stir until slightly moistened.
Fold in raisins. Grease muffin tin and preheat oven to 400°.
Fill 2/3 full. Bake 18 to 20 minutes. Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon sugar over each muffin.

title: baked grits
directions: Cook grits in salted water for 8 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bake in casserole for 1 hour at 300°.
Sprinkle top with margarine and paprika.

title: chicken poulet de normande
directions: Mix chicken, mayonnaise, onion, celery and salt together.
Set aside.
Mix broth, oleo and dressing together.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan with Pam; put half of dressing in bottom of pan. Place chicken mixture on top.
Put remaining dressing on top. Beat eggs and milk together and pour over casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Take out of refrigerator 1 hour before baking; spread soup on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Take out, sprinkle with cheese and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Pour boiling water on gelatin in large bowl:
stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Mix apricot and pineapple syrups; reserve 1 cup.
Measure remaining syrup; add enough water to measure 1 cup. Stir syrup-water mixture into gelatin mixture.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened, about 1 hour.

title: raspberry cheesecake
directions: Combine the cracker crumbs, almonds, 1/4 cup of the sugar, 2 tablespoons of the flour and butter.
Press onto the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a medium bowl, combine the sugar, flour, cream cheese, liqueur and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add the eggs and yogurt, beating on low speed until combined.
Pour into the pan.
Place the pan on a shallow baking pan in the oven. Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Loosen the cake from the sides of the pan.
Cool another 30 minutes and remove the sides of the pan.
Chill at least four hours.
Top with fresh raspberries and powdered sugar.

title: apple-cheese casserole
directions: Line bottom of casserole dish with apples.
Cream the cheese, sugar, flour and buttermilk until smooth.
Cover apples with cheese mixture.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cracker spread
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake and cool pie crust.
Boil for 3 minutes the mixture of frozen strawberries, sugar and water, stirring constantly.
Add cornstarch (dissolved) and mix thoroughly.
Remove from heat. Cool to at least room temperature.
Line the cooled pie crust with halved fresh berries.
Pour cooled mixture over.
Refrigerate. Top with whipped cream.

title: ratatouille (french vegetable stew)
directions: In large Dutch oven or very large saucepan, heat oil. Saute onions, garlic and peppers until tender, about 5 minutes. Add zucchini, summer squash, eggplant, tomatoes and spices. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low. Simmer covered for 35 to 45 minutes depending on how crisp you like your vegetables.
Serve hot or cold. Garnish with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: naomi's apple salad
directions: Heat applesauce.
Mix jello in hot applesauce.
Pour 7-Up into mixture and stir well.
Pour into bowl or jello mold.
Place in refrigerator until congealed.

title: coconut marshmallow goodies(uncooked)
directions: Combine sugar, butter and eggs in top of double boiler.
Cook 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix.
Turn into 8 x 10-inch pan. Refrigerate.
This will get solid in a day or several hours.

title: quiche
directions: Combine
and
pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: west virginia corn bake
directions: Brown meat in fat.
Add onion and pepper.
Remove from heat. Combine with meat mixture.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart baking or casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 standard muffin pan cups. Beat together butter, eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in bananas until smooth.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add to egg mixture until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Do not overmix.
Spoon into pans and fill each cup 2/3 full.
Bake until golden brown, 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool in pans slightly before removing.

title: taffy-apple pizza
directions: Roll out cookie dough onto a rectangular baking pan or stone. Bake according to pkg directions. Set aside to cool. Mix peanut butter, vanilla, and cream cheese together and spread over cookie then arrange the sliced and cored apples over the peanut butter mixture. Use the remaining ingredients as garnish.

title: cool whip graveyard treat
directions: Mix 2 cups cookie crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 stick oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press into bottom of pan and refrigerate.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Combine salmon, onion, eggs, seasoning, flour and Accent in large mixing bowl; blend well.
Shape into patties.
Place Crisco into large skillet on medium heat.
Place patties in hot oil and fry 3 minutes on each side.
Remove from heat; drain and cool. Yields 8 croquettes.

title: quick beef and bean casserole
directions: In large iron skillet or pan, brown meat.
Drain.
Add chopped onion.
Cook, stirring often, until onion begins to look transparent.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add water, if needed, to make enough juice for cooking.
Cover and reduce heat to simmer.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: sweet roll rings
directions: Dissolve yeast with 3/4 cup warm water; set aside.
In large bowl, mix sugar, butter, salt and hot water; let cool.
Add egg, yeast water and flour.
Let rise, punch down.
Divide into 3 parts. Roll into rectangles.
Cover with soft butter.
Sprinkle with sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll rectangles up lengthwise. Form a circle; pinch together.
Cut slits across top with scissors. Turn up angles.
Let rise.
Cook at 400° until brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Sugar glaze (powdered sugar and hot water).
Trim with pecans and cherries.

title: judy's applesauce cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost with any frosting you wish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Can also add nuts or raisins.

title: diabetic pineapple-orange marmalade
directions: Drain juice from pineapple into saucepan.
Sprinkle gelatin on juice.
Wait 1 minute until it is soft, then heat gently until gelatin melts.
Remove from heat and stir in crushed pineapple, thawed orange juice concentrate and low calorie sweetener.
Store in covered jars in refrigerator.

title: broccoli and feta pasta
directions: Saute broccoli in olive oil 2 to 3 minutes.
Add next four ingredients and simmer 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and add crumbled Feta.
Heat, do not boil.
Toss with 8 ounces cooked pasta. Serves four.

title: lentil-walnut burgers(vegetarian)
directions: Place lentils and water in small saucepan and bring to a boil. Lower the heat and simmer, partially covered, for about 30 minutes or until the lentils are soft and the liquid is gone. Transfer to a medium bowl.
Add vinegar and mash well.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in 1 tablespoon margarine or Pam. (Use a wok or large nonstick frying pan.)
You may want to add more margarine or Pam throughout this recipe.
Add chicken and stir-fry until tender and completely cooked.
You can add a little water occasionally to keep chicken and vegetables from drying out or sticking.
Sprinkle with 1 to 2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Add florets and stir-fry until slightly tender, but still crunchy.
Add squash and stir-fry until slightly tender.
Add rest of soy sauce and stir-fry.
You may want to season with salt and pepper now to taste.
Remove from heat.
Serve over rice or saffron rice.

title: homemade dog biscuits
directions: Combine all dry ingredients, except yeast.
In separate bowl, dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add chicken broth (can use bouillon, pan drippings or water from cooking vegetables).
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Knead mixture for about 3 minutes. Dough will be quite stiff.
If too stiff, add extra liquid or an egg.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Roll dough on floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Immediately cut into shape with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; brush with a wash of egg and milk.
Place in oven.
After 75 minutes, turn off oven and cover biscuits overnight in oven to get bone hard.

title: diet in a glass
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender. Process until well blended. Chill before serving.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Make Jell-O.
Stir in sherbet until dissolved.
Add fruit and let set.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Peel and cut potatoes. Boil until tender, about one hour. Drain and mash. Add butter, sugar, and milk; stir. Add vanilla and eggs; stir. Add pineapple, orange juice and marshmallows. Stir. Add nuts, if desired. Bake about one hour at 350° or until top looks dry. Serves 4-6.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Mix all.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours for flavors to blend.

title: asparagus loaf
directions: Melt margarine.
Add crackers and stir until well mixed and color changes.
Mix together eggs, milk, onion and salt.
Add crackers and asparagus; mix again.
Turn into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until set.
Heat soup with milk; mix in melted cheese, pour over loaf and serve.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan on low heat.
Stir in flour.
Add milk.
Stir constantly until desired thickness.
Add salt and pepper.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, cinnamon and butter until crumbly.
Press half of mixture into 8 x 8 pan.
Cover with rhubarb.

title: lana zirbel's spinach dip
directions: Add some garlic, onion salt, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix and bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: christmas fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with Cool Whip.

title: peanut patties
directions: Combine
sugar,
Karo,	milk
and
peanuts
in	a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil, then simmer on low, low heat for 1 1/2 to 2
hours, uncovered.
Stir occasionally.
When it forms a soft ball in
cold water, set off fire.	Add oleo and vanilla.
Beat until creamy and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: apple pie squares
directions: Mix flour, shortening, butter and salt like pie crust.
Add egg yolk mixture and mix.
Roll half and put in large jelly roll pan.
Top with crushed corn flakes.

title: happiness cake
directions: Combine patience, love and generosity with understanding; add a dash of laughter and sprinkle with kindness.
Add plenty of faith; mix well.
Spread over a period of a lifetime.
Serve to everyone you meet.
Sit back, relax and enjoy a slice or two every day of the year.

title: caramel icing
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar in iron skillet.

While this is browning, put all other ingredients in a thick cooker and bring to a boil. Add the browned sugar and let it all cook together for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and beat until ready to put on cake.
Good on yellow or spice cake.
Very good and easy.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: Rub wall of crock-pot (1-quart size) with butter.
Place chocolate, marshmallows and milk in crock-pot.
Cover and cook, stirring every 30 minutes until melted.
Gradually add up to 1/2 cup whipping cream until desired thickness.
Serve with pound cake, angel food cake, pretzels or fruit or use as a topping on ice cream.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, white sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in gradually the following:
flour, oatmeal, baking soda, corn flakes, coconut, nuts and salt.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 325° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: easy pudding cake
directions: Prepare pudding, following package directions; let cool. Blend cake mix into cooled pudding; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over top of cake.
Cook according to cake mix directions. Cut when cool.

title: scallop potatoes
directions: Layer in baking dish the potatoes and cheese.
Mix onion, cream of chicken soup and cream of mushroom soup and put a layer of this mixture.
Add 1 tablespoon milk.
Continue layering until you have your desired amount.
Bake at 300° until potatoes are tender.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Divide popcorn between 2 ungreased rectangular pans, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Heat brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until bubbly around edges.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour over popcorn; stir until well coated.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 15 cups of snack.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup boiling water.
Heat soup and dissolve cream cheese in soup.
Add gelatin to soup and cheese and cool.
Add mayonnaise, onion, celery and salt.
When thickened, add shrimp and turn into mold that has been dipped in cold water.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Combine first seven ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Spread peaches over batter.
Beat cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons reserved peach juice.
Spread over top of batter; leave about 1/2-inch all the way around.
On top, sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar and milk.
Bring to a good boil.
Take from heat and stir in confectioners sugar until smooth.
Stir in vanilla well.

title: parmesan dijon chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix mustard, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and butter in small bowl.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and parsley in large plastic bag.
Brush mustard mixture on chicken, then shake chicken in bag to coat with crumb mixture.
Place chicken, skin side up, in ungreased rectangular baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, 50 to 60 minutes or until juice is no longer pink when centers of thickest pieces are cut.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Pour into a well-buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can make ahead and refrigerate; allow 20 minutes extra baking time.

title: green chili enchilada casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream; heat up.
Fry corn tortillas.
Layer tortillas with warmed mixture, onions, chilies and grated cheeses. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken with cashew nuts
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients; shape into an 8-inch loaf.
Place on a lightly greased rack of a broiler pan; top with tomato slices.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: vegetarian cabbage rolls
directions: Cut large leaves from a head of cabbage (place in hot water) to blanch leaves.
Combine the rest of the following ingredients together.
Mix well and form into rolls; wrap with cabbage leaf. Secure with a toothpick.
Place rolls in pan and add tomato sauce. Cook in a 350° oven for an hour or until tender.

title: caramel penuche
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine in large glass bowl.
Cook in microwave over 2 minutes; mix well.
Continue cooking 5 minutes.
Add caramels.
Continue cooking 45 seconds.
Beat vigorously until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Add nuts; mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 8-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: lentil loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Place in an oiled 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake for 45 minutes.
Lentil loaf is so moist that it needs no gravy or sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon pepper fish roll-ups
directions: Roll fillets and arrange in microwave-safe dish.
Combine melted margarine, lemon juice and peel and pepper.
Spoon over fish rolls and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover loosely with wax paper.
Cook on High for 3 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and cook 2 minutes longer, if necessary.
Or, bake in 450° oven, uncovered, for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: cornflake chicken
directions: Beat together milk, egg, salt, pepper and paprika.
Dip chicken in this mixture; roll in crushed cornflakes and place in a well-greased casserole dish or pan.
Crumble crushed cornflakes on top and dribble a little milk on this.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican salad
directions: Layer all the ingredients in the order given.

title: oven apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in large stainless steel or heavy aluminum bowl or pan. Bake at 350° for 3 hours, stirring occasionally. Put in jars and seal.

title: smokie cheese crescents
directions: In food processor or mixer, cream the two cheeses together until smooth.
Unroll the crescent rolls.
Cut each triangle into 3 equal pieces.
Spread small amount of cheese on each small crescent piece.
Wrap a Smok-Y-Link in each one.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until golden brown, about 10 minutes.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Soak lima beans overnight.
Cook until just tender.
Place drained pears in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover with drained lima beans.
Sprinkle with onion salt.
Pour over enough reserved pear juice to cover. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Baste every 15 minutes with melted butter.
Cover with bacon crumbs before serving.

title: rice cake candy bar
directions: Spread peanut butter evenly on rice cakes.
Drizzle 1 teaspoon chocolate syrup on top of each; sprinkle evenly with raisins and cinnamon.
Makes 2.
Each serving provides:

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together well and chill overnight.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Set aside caps and mince stems.
Heat oil and saute chopped beef and mushroom stems; add all other ingredients and blend well.
Cook for about 5 minutes. Spoon into caps and place on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 20 or 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: impossible lasagna pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease a 10-inch pie plate. Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese in plate. Mix beef, oregano, basil, tomato paste and 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese. Spoon over top. Beat milk, baking mix, eggs, salt and pepper until smooth. Pour into plate. Bake until knife comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Cool 5 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sally's chuck wagon
directions: Scramble (cook) ground beef in oleo.
Add a few shakes of Worcestershire sauce.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients, simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with biscuits.

title: one-step lasagna
directions: Spread about 1 cup spaghetti sauce in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix cottage cheese with yogurt.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease pan and spread pineapple and cherry pie filling and cake mix dry from the box.
Top with nuts; dot with margarine. Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Serve hot or cold.
Cut in squares.

title: festive appetizer quiche
directions: Sprinkle Swiss cheese and shrimp over bottom of pastry shell. Beat eggs with cream, chives, salt, dry mustard and nutmeg.
Pour over cheese and shrimp.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 20 minutes before serving. Cut in thick slices.
May be served warm or chilled.

title: fried fish
directions: Combine corn meal, salt, flour, and onion powder.
Dredge fish in mixture, coating both sides.
Deep fry in hot oil for 3 to 5 minutes, or until brown.
Drain.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix warm sweet potatoes with sugar, salt and Crisco.
Add flour and mix well.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: donna's poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Beat 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 floured and greased loaf pans.
Bake 45 minutes.
Needs no frosting.

title: parmesan baked vidalias
directions: Peel and slice onions into 5/8-inch strips.
Cook in boiling salted water until half done.
This is important.
Drain in colander.
Butter an 8-inch square casserole.
Place 1/3 of the crushed crackers, butter and Parmesan.
Repeat layers, using 1/3 each time.
Sprinkle the milk over all.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until onions are done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: randy's cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat egg slightly with milk. Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add shortening.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef with onion. Drain. Combine rest of ingredients with beef mixture. Simmer 30 minutes. Keep over low heat until ready to serve. Serve with large dip size Fritos.

title: watermelon juice summertime
directions: In a large bowl, cut watermelon in small pieces; add 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 3 1/2 cups ice and two cups of water. Mix together, stirring until sugar has dissolved.
Serve on hot day.

title: four day pickles
directions: First day: In the morning, wash and cut up cucumbers; place in a large container and cover with boiling water. That afternoon (or 6 or 7 hours later), drain and cover with fresh boiling water. Second day; In the morning, drain and cover with fresh boiling water. That afternoon, drain and add 1/2 c. salt and cover with fresh boiling water.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Chill several hours.

title: crab casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour to butter.
Gradually add milk until smooth.
Add crabmeat, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with breadcrumbs and cheese.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix and bake in oven at 350°.

title: creamy potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets until tender; peel and shred. Combine shredded potatoes with sour cream, onions, 3/4 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Turn mixture into buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Add peanut butter, then stir.
Add Rice Krispies and stir.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips together.
Spread over cookie mixture while still warm.
Cool, then eat.

title: microwave hot buttered rum
directions: In a mug, mix sugar and rum.
Fill cup to 2/3 full of water. Cook on High until very hot, but not boiling.
Add butter, nutmeg and cinnamon stick.
Makes 1 serving.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine flour, sugar, milk and eggs in bowl; beat until smooth. Heat 1/2-inch oil to 375° in electric skillet.
Pour 1/4 cup of batter into funnel.
Drizzle into hot oil in spiral pattern, controlling flow with finger.
Fry for one minute on each side or until golden brown; drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Yield:
1 dozen.

title: cheese broccoli
directions: Boil broccoli and drain.
Mix with Cheez Whiz and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spanish steak
directions: Brown steak; spread with remaining ingredients.
Bake in lid covered pan at 350° for 2 hours.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Pour 2 cups hot water over molasses, sugar, salt and shortening.
Mix and cool.
Then add yeast and stir.
Mix in flour to desired stiffness.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli and chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until tender.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook broccoli in salted water 5 minutes and drain.
Make sauce of soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice.
In oblong casserole, place layer of broccoli, layer of chicken and pour sauce over contents.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over top. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: polly's quick banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding by directions on box. Then set aside. Mix in 1/2 Cool Whip and condensed milk. Crumble a few vanilla wafers on bottom of large clear glass bowl to cover bottom. Cover crumbs with some pudding mixture. Place a layer of sliced bananas on top of this. Cover this with evenly spaced whole vanilla wafers. Continue alternating layers until all ingredients are used up. Use rest of Cool Whip on top. Refrigerate overnight if possible.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Cook beef and drain off grease.
Mix remaining ingredients with beef and cook on low heat for 1 hour.

title: zesty tortillas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Mix soup, sour cream and chilies.
Fill tortillas with hamburger, cheese and 2 tablespoons of sauce.
Roll and put in pan.
Cover with remainder of sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May add jalapenos, tomatoes, olives, etc.

title: easy chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Rinse chicken.
Cook in water to cover in saucepan until tender.
Remove chicken, reserving 1 1/2 cups broth.
Bone chicken and cut into pieces.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread soups over chicken.
Pour milk over soups.
Combine margarine, stuffing mix and reserved chicken broth in bowl; mix well.
Spoon over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with tossed salad.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: eggs for a bunch
directions: Saute in butter, onions, mushrooms and ham.
Beat until frothy the eggs and milk, then scramble.
Mix together eggs, ham, 1 can mushroom soup and diced cheese.
Bake at 225° until bubbly.

title: apple cake #1
directions: Mix as for pie dough (use fork).
Use a little more than 1/2 of the dough for bottom of jelly roll pan.
Use crushed corn flakes next, sliced apples, 3/4 cup sugar and sprinkle on some cinnamon.
Roll out top layer and put on top.
Prick with fork. Beat egg white and brush on top.
Bake at 375° for one hour.
When done, drizzle with a light frosting.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: *Can substitute 1 (8 ounce) sour cream dip with peppers and 1 package Mexican corn bread mix.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream the oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Sift and mix the dry ingredients into the creamed mixture.
Stir in the nuts and apples.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
The pan can be an oblong cake pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: honey-lime dressing
directions: Combine ingredients.
Beat to blend.
Store in jar in refrigerator.
Serve over mixed fruit.

title: peanut butter chicken for grilling
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry with paper towels. Mix marinade as follows. Stir hot water into a small bowl with the peanut butter (mixture will stiffen at first). Stir in the rest of the ingredients and mix well. Place chicken in a plastic bag in a shallow bowl. Pour marinade over the chicken and seal the bag, turning it so that all chicken pieces are covered. Chill for 12 to 24 hours. Drain off marinade and discard. Grill chicken over medium hot coals, 35 to 45 minutes until done. Serve with salsa or fresh fruit or any bottled fruit salsa.

title: soft lemon cookies
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, salt and food coloring, blend thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Roll out small portion of dough at a time; cut with cookie cutters.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: quick fixin' casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together in skillet.
Drain fat. Return to skillet and add taco seasoning mix, water and 1/2 cup picante sauce.
Mix and simmer about 5 minutes.
In a 3-quart casserole dish, layer ingredients in this order:
half of the hamburger mixture, a layer of Fritos, half of the cheese and half of the picante sauce. Repeat for second layer. Cook in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: bon voyage chicken
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add bell pepper; saut 4 minutes.
Add tomatoes; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add pasta and black pepper, stirring well.
Place about 1 1/2 cups pasta mixture into each of 4 bowls; top each.
Serving with 1 tablespoon basil and 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese.
Serve with Caesar salad and bread.

title: frosting (fudge)
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil, then add sugar, vanilla and chopped pecans.
Pour on warm cake.

title: hard candy
directions: Mix together sugar, corn syrup and water in a large saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, until temperature reaches 310° or until drops of syrup form hard, brittle threads in cold water.
Remove from heat; after boiling has stopped, stir in flavoring and coloring.
Pour onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight containers.
Makes in excess of 2 pounds.

title: turkey or chicken divan
directions: Steam broccoli 10 minutes; drain.
Place poultry in bottom of greased lasagna pan, then broccoli and rice.
Combine soup, milk and cheese.
Pour over contents; stir carefully so as not to break the broccoli.
Cover with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until mixture is hot.
Great way to use up leftover turkey.

title: chinese chews
directions: Melt morsels, one package at a time, until all are soft enough to coat the noodles and peanuts.
Mix, then drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper or greased cookie sheet.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn bread mix.
Add corn bread mix last and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: five can casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Simmer hen in water, salted to taste for about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Cool.
Remove meat from bones, reserving liquid for Dressing.

title: biscotti toscani
directions: Place nuts in shallow pan and bake in a preheated 325° oven until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.
In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, vanilla, almond extract and orange zest.
In a bowl combine the flour, baking powder, nutmeg and salt.
Add to the creamed mixture, mixing until blended.
Cut almonds into halves or thirds and fold in.
Divide dough in half.
Place on a greased and floured baking sheet and form into two logs about 1/2-inch thick, 1 1/2 inches wide and 12 inches long, spacing them at least 2 inches apart.
Bake in the middle of a preheated 325° oven for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Transfer to a baking rack and let cool 5 minutes.
Place on a cutting board.
With a serrated knife, slice diagonally at a 45° angle about 1/2-inch thick.
Lay the slices flat on the baking sheet and return to the oven for 10 minutes, turning them over once to dry slightly.
Let cool on a rack.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Saute onion, mushrooms and beef in butter over medium heat. Remove and mix in cooked rice.
Add to cabbage leaves and roll up; secure with toothpick.
Place in pan and pour tomatoes and their juice over rolls.
Sprinkle with salt and sugar.
Cover; turn heat on medium until cover is hot.
Reduce to low and cook for 20 minutes or until cabbage is done.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill thoroughly before serving.

title: cranberry-orange sauce for ham
directions: Mix Sweet 'N Low, cornstarch and salt together in saucepan. Add orange juice, cranberry juice and raisins.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Pour sauce over sliced ham.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yield:
2 cups or 21 servings of 1 1/2 tablespoons each. Exchanges:
1 1/2 tablespoons = 1/2 fruit.
Calories:
1 1/2 tablespoons = 21.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil until tender.
Add green peppers and saute.
Add remaining ingredients except flour and kidney beans.
Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes.
Mix flour in 3 tablespoons water.
Add to mixture along with beans.

title: hot-hot-hot-pickles
directions: Let vinegar, salt and
water come to a boil.
Pour over pickles; seal while still
hot.
Let
set
to 3 weeks, turn once a week.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling, salted water.
Drain and arrange in shallow, 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Simmer chicken in small amount of water for 35 minutes or until tender.
Drain and arrange on broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, juice and curry power.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.

title: butterscotch refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Form into 1-inch rolls, wrap in waxed paper.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Slice into thin slices with a sharp knife.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry-raspberry ring
directions: Dissolve gelatins in boiling water;
stir in frozen raspberries and cranberry-orange relish.
Add club soda and lemon juice.
Turn into an oiled 6-cup ring mold.
Chill overnight. Unmold on lettuce lined serving plate.
Serve with sour cream, if desired.
Makes 10 servings.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Toast and bake nuts at 375 for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Watch carefully usually take about 8 minutes. Cool.

title: fried squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by spoon in hot grease in skillet. Cook until brown. Turn once to brown other side.

title: kentucky fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in tube pan.

title: white chili
directions: In
large
saucepan,
combine
water,
lemon pepper and cumin seed.
Bring
to
boil, then add chicken breast halves. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 20 to 28 minutes or until chicken is
fork-tender and juices run clear.
Remove chicken from
bones; cut into 1-inch pieces or shred.
Return chicken to
saucepan. Spray
medium
skillet with cooking spray; heat over medium heat. Add garlic clove, cook and stir one minute. Remove
from
pan
and add to chicken mixture.
Add onions to skillet.
Cook
and
stir until
tender.
Add
cooked onions, corn,
chilies, ground cumin and 2 to 3 tablespoons lime juice to
chicken
mixture.
Bring
to a
boil.
Add beans and cook until thoroughly heated.

title: low fat ambrosia
directions: Put pineapple and oranges in large bowl, sprinkle pudding over and stir until mixed.
Add the rest of the ingredients, mix until well blended.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
One cup equals 3 points on Weight Watchers.

title: beer cheese
directions: Beat cheese, garlic, pepper and onion.
Add beer a little at a time; continue beating until the consistency you want.

title: cream of carrot and leek soup
directions: Sift soup mix.
Combine with other ingredients.
Heat until thickened, but do not boil.
Garnish with a dollop of plain yogurt and a sprinkling of chives or dill weed.
(Reserve the reconstituted vegetables from soup mix for casseroles, salads, etc.)
Serves 3 to 4.

title: vegetarian chili(from the vegetarian times magazine)
directions: Drain tomatoes into pot.
Bring 1 cup of the liquid to boil. Remove heat and stir in bulgar.
Cover and let stand 30 minutes. In skillet with little bit of oil cook veggies except green pepper, cover skillet.
Add green pepper after 10 minutes and cook 10 minutes more.
Veggies should not be mushy.
Combine everything and cook just until heated.

title: dieter's delight
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed on package.
Let Jell-O set until almost firm.
Add other ingredients and mix into Jell-O. Refrigerate Jell-O until solid firm.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, syrup, salt, milk and 3/4 cup water.
Bring to boil, cover and cook for 2 minutes.
Uncover and cook, without stirring, until soft ball stage (232°).
Remove from heat.
Cool to lukewarm and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until mixture thickens and loses its gloss.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Beat cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Mix softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs together.
Pour over first mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in oven at 300° for about 20 or 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot roast beef dinner
directions: Place roast beef in crock-pot, sprinkle liberally with Worcestershire sauce.
Add bay leaves.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix on top of roast.
Add prepared vegetables, fitting around and on top of roast.
Spread 2 cans soup over all.
Cook on low at least 8 hours.
Gravy may be thickened before serving.

title: spanish omelet
directions: Cut the potatoes into 1/2-inch squares, adding salt to them as you go along.
Fry the potatoes with a low flame, stirring them once in a while.
When they are soft, add the finely chopped onions to the potatoes.
The potatoes and onions should be very soft and not too golden.

title: molded cranberry relish or salad
directions: Cook cranberries in 1 cup of water for 20 minutes.
Stir in sugar and cook 5 minutes longer.
Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup of cold water; add to hot cranberries and stir until dissolved. Cool.
When mixture begins to thicken, add chopped celery, nuts and salt.
Turn into a favorite dish or mold and chill in refrigerator.

title: ranchers stew
directions: Saute meat and onions until onions are tender.
Pour the rest of the ingredients in meat mixture and simmer for 1 hour.

title: maple pecan pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well. Sprinkle pecans evenly on bottom of pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over pecans. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake for 35 minutes or until set.
Good!

title: hillbilly goulash
directions: Fry ground beef unti it crumbles.
Drain off lard.
Put pork and beans in large pot.
Add 1/2 can of tomato sauce and garlic salt.
Add ground beef and stir.
Cook on low, stirring occasionally, for about 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes a great one pot dinner.

title: swedish chicken casserole
directions: Cover bottom of pan with dried beef.
Wrap chicken pieces with a strip of bacon, then lay chicken on top of dried beef.
Mix 1 can of cream of chicken soup and 1 cup of sour cream and pour over chicken.
Cover and cook at 275° for 3 hours.

title: chocolate peanut pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, brown sugar, chocolate and 1/4 cup milk in saucepan.
Add egg yolks and blend well.
Add remaining	1
3/4 cups
milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly
until mix comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in butter.	Cool at least 5 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times.

title: sugar cookies 2
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and flavoring thoroughly.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt together.
Blend all together and chill at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured board.
Cut with 3-inch cutter. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until cookies are a delicate golden color.
Makes about 4 dozen.
Frost if desired.

title: jogger's nog
directions: Combine ingredients in blender container.
Cover and run on high until well blended.
Serve in chilled glasses.
Yields 2 servings (10 ounces each).

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Combine fruit, 1/2 cup of sugar and 2 tablespoons of flour. Place in an 8-inch square pan coated with Pam.
Dot with butter. Combine remaining ingredients and drop by spoonfuls over fruit. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs and add oleo.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder or Bisquick and salt; add to egg mixture.
Slowly add milk and stir in coconut and vanilla.
Pour into 2 greased pie pans with no crust (it makes its own crust).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 2 pies.
It's so easy and delicious!

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: In saucepan, combine milk and flour; stir until smooth.
Add margarine, chicken bouillon powder, paprika, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Add 2 cups shredded cheese and stir until smooth.
Spread potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cheese mixture over potatoes and mix lightly.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese grits
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in an ungreased casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: veggie bars - squares - pizza
directions: Buy 1/2 gallon of dill pickles; drain off juice.
Boil 3 cups sugar and 1 cup water.
(While this is boiling, slice pickles in chunks the way you like to serve them.)
After slicing, put back in jar and pour hot liquid over them.
In one week, ready to serve.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: gooey butter coffee cake
directions: For crust, combine cake mix, melted butter and egg.
Mix and press evenly into a 12 x 18-inch pan (it will be thin).
Sprinkle with 1 cup of nuts (pecans).

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, onions and salt, in enough water to cover, for 2 hours.
Drain.
Cook until tender with vinegar and spices.
Seal in sterilized bottles.

title: fruit punch
directions: Dilute juices with water.
Add ginger ale and mix.
Sweeten to taste.

title: walnut filling
directions: Mix ingredients together in a large heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet.
Mix first five ingredients.
Pour half the batter into greased skillet.
Add in layers, meat, peppers, onion and cheese, then top with remainder of batter.
Bake one hour at 375°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sour cream brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine water, margarine and chocolate in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in flour and then sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream, soda and salt; mix well.
Pour into jellyroll pan; bake for 20 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain real well.
Mix taco seasoning with hamburger.
Spread sour cream in bottom of shallow dish.
Spread hamburger mixture over sour cream; top with cheese, lettuce, tomatoes or any other optional ingredients.

title: pear honey
directions: Chop pears finely (not pureed); measure pears to equal 4 cups. Combine pears and sugar in heavy saucepan.
Bring mixture slowly to a boil, stirring frequently, until sugar dissolves.
Reduce heat; simmer 45 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add drained pineapple.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Spoon hot mixture into hot sterilized jars.
Leave 1/4-inch headspace.
Wipe jar rims.
Cover at once with metal sterilized lids.
Screw on bands.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yields 6 1/2 pints.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in medium size cake pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs and beat well; add pineapple.
Sift the dry ingredients and add to first mixture and beat well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased and floured cookie sheet and bake until light brown at 375°.

title: squash corn bread
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Add meal, cottage cheese and squash. Pour into well greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle with margarine. Bake in a 375° oven for 40 minutes.
Makes 15 servings.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Layer sliced bananas and vanilla wafers in serving dish.
Fold Cool Whip and sour cream into vanilla pudding and pour over bananas and wafers.
Sprinkle top with crushed wafers and chopped nuts.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water. Add cold water, drained crushed pineapple and pie filling. Pour into large dish.
Let congeal.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese and sugar.
Spread this on top.
Sprinkle with pecan pieces.

title: pecan bars
directions: Bake 15 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix together. Cover to keep from icing and freeze.
Use as salad or dessert.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla with sour cream, soda and salt.
Then add flour, raisins, coconut and nuts.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until light brown.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry icing
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add strawberries, pecans and coconut. Mix well.
Spread between layers.
Drizzle down side of cake and do the top.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Beat
eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: fluffy orange pie
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press firmly on bottom and up side to rim of 9-inch pie plate.
Chill.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then juice concentrate until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream and pour into crust.
Chill 2 hours or until set. Garnish as desired.
Makes one 9-inch pie.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fruit squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Beat in egg. Add vanilla.
Take half of mixture and put in 8 x 10-inch pan. Cover with prepared pie filling.
To other half mixture, add heaping tablespoon of brown sugar and a pinch of cinnamon.
Spread on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Mix this, getting lumps out.
Add 1/4 cup milk.
Use plastic/wooden spoon.
Lay 1 stick oleo on top of mix.
Place in microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Remove and stir.
Place in microwave for another minute.
Butter rectangular #1 Mod Mate. Pour fudge.
Place in fridge to set.

title: linguine with mushrooms and garlic sauce
directions: In large pot, boil water for pasta.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Add garlic; allow to brown for a minute, then add mushrooms, basil and salt and cook until mushrooms are just tender.
Add remaining 4 tablespoons butter, pepper and oil; stir and remove from heat.
Cook linguine until al dente.
When pasta is done, reheat sauce and add parsley.
Drain pasta; pour into medium size bowl, along with sauce, and toss.
Serve with Parmesan cheese on the side.

title: quicky cobbler(low-fat, no sugar)
directions: Microwave fruit in baking dish until heated through.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Drop onto fruit.
Microwave on High about 6 minutes until breading is done.
(It will not be browned.)
Put each serving in a bowl.
Sprinkle with 1 packet Equal.
Top with skim milk.
Good with sugar-free vanilla ice cream, but it has fat.
Yield:
4 large servings.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Line bottom of casserole with 1 1/2 cups of raw rice.
Lay slices of onion, tomato and bell pepper on top of rice.
Lay browned (not floured) pork chops on top of this.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour beef consomme and water over dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in covered casserole.

title: tortellini in herb-garlic dressing
directions: Cook tortellini in boiling salted water until tender but still firm.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Place in bowl.

title: no mind pie
directions: In a 9 inch pie plate, mix all ingredients and form a crust.

title: carousel cookies
directions: You can use strawberry, raspberry or apricot preserves.

title: banana doughnuts
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Combine rest of ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well; add dry ingredients to banana mixture.
Mix well.
Turn out onto a very well floured board.
Roll dough to a thickness of 1/4-inch and cut with a well floured doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep fat heated to 375°, until evenly browned.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Grease pans and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Keep checking toward end. Let the loaves cool for 15 minutes and then turn out and wrap immediately in foil and seal tightly.
Bread will be very moist. Makes 2 large loaves or 3 small loaves.

title: ice cream in a cloud
directions: Let egg whites	come
to
room temperature.
In a small mixing bowl, beat together whites, vanilla and cream of tartar until soft peaks
form.
Gradually add sugar and beat to stiff peaks and until
nearly
all of the sugar is dissolved.
Cover baking sheet with plain, ungreased brown paper or foil; draw a 10-inch circle. Spoon
about 15 dollops (2/3 of the meringue) just inside circle, making sides of shell 1-inch high.	Spread remaining meringue inside
circle,
making
bottom
of
shell 1/2-inch thick.	Bake at	300° for 45 minutes.
Turn off heat and let dry
in
oven (door
closed) at least 1 hour.
Remove from oven;	cool. Transfer
meringue	shell
to
12-inch
pie taker.	Soften ice cream
and	stir; spread half of chocolate ice cream into
shell. Top
with all of the cherry ice cream, spreading evenly.
Drop remaining ice cream by spoonfuls over cherry layer, then
swirl. Freeze
for several hours or overnight.

title: polynesian pork roast
directions: Place meat in roaster; combine nutmeg, thyme, salt and pepper and sprinkle over meat.
Cover and roast at 325° for 2 hours.

title: miniature drumsticks
directions: Cut wings in half. Discard wing tips.
Combine flour, cheese and seasonings in shallow dish. Dip chicken pieces in buttermilk. Shake to remove excess. Roll in flour mixture.
Heat oil in electric skillet to 365°.
Fry chicken pieces for 5 minutes. Drain on absorbent paper.
Keep warm.
Yields 18 servings.

title: cream of wheat cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken and pick apart.
Mix Stove Top by directions on box.
Use broth from chicken in place of water.
Add soup and mayonnaise.
Place chicken on bottom of casserole dish.
Mix together and bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rich, coffee flavored ice cream pie(turtle ice cream pie)
directions: Soften coffee flavored ice cream.
Stir and fill the 9-inch chocolate graham cracker pie shell.
Freeze until firm.
Top with approximately 1/2 jar caramel topping.
Freeze until firm.
Spread 1/2 jar Nutella and sprinkle with pecan pieces.
Freeze until firm.

title: hawaiian bread dip
directions: Cut top of bread.
Hollow out into the shape of a bowl.
Mix all ingredients, put into bread bowl and place top back on.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Take out of foil, remove top. Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: aunt jessie miller's goulash
directions: Mix all ingredients except milk.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Pour milk over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old fashion egg custard
directions: Beat all together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf(diabetic recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add just enough water to form a firm ball.
Press into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Prepare rice as directed on box. Add all ingredients and warm.

title: "s" cookies
directions: Set oven temperature at 350°.
In a large bowl, mix all the dry ingredients; make a well in the middle and put eggs, vanilla and melted butter.
Blend with a fork until all blended.
Mix everything together.
Take pieces of dough, enough to shape into an "S" and bake until brown on bottom (not too brown).
When cool, ice with confectioners sugar and milk.
Sprinkle with confetti. Let icing dry before storing.

title: protka
directions: Combine onion, ground beef, water chestnuts and garlic powder in a bowl.
Spoon onto egg roll wraps and roll up.
Cook in oil over medium heat until meat is done inside.
Turn frequently so they won't burn.
Drain on paper towel.
Cut into thirds.
Dip in sauce.

title: all saints sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Heat until warm.
Serves 10 plus.

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients and heat slowly.
Remove wing tips; dejoint middle and upper pieces.
Marinate wings for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
(I usually let them stand overnight in a tightly closed baggie, turning occasionally.)
Put in shallow pan and bake in oven for 1 hour at 275°, turn and baste wings and bake 40 minutes at 300°.
Wings will be dark and glazed.

title: great pizza crust
directions: You can do this by hand or bread mixer.
Raise about 20 minutes or until you need it.
Bake at 400°.
I bake crust 10 minutes before putting topping on.
This makes large pizza or 2 small.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Pour the well-beaten eggs over the other ingredients except Miracle Whip and cook very slowly until thick, stirring constantly.
Whe cool, add Miracle Whip.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut Twinkies lengthwise; place in bottom of pan, cream side up.
Mix pudding as directed on package; pour over Twinkies.
Smooth out so it covers the cake.
Slice strawberries in half; layer over pudding.
Spread Cool Whip over strawberries.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients, spread in pan.
Mix remaining 3 ingredients, spread on top.
Bake 45 minutes in 300° oven.

title: grandma's banana bread
directions: Put sugar, butter and eggs in large bowl; beat well.
Add mashed bananas and 1/2 cup flour; beat well.
Mix soda in 3 tablespoons hot water and add with remaining ingredients.
Mix well with spoon.
Line pan with foil.
Bake 1 hour in slow oven at 300°.

title: kahlua mousse
directions: Beat egg yolks and 2 tablespoons Kahlua in the top of a double boiler. Beat in 1/4 cup sugar and beat until slightly thickened and color lightens. Place pan over boiling water. Cook and stir until thickened, about 10 minutes. Set top of double boiler in bowl of cold water. Beat until mixture is thick, 3 to 4 minutes.

title: 7-up party salad
directions: Combine 7-Up and marshmallows in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until marshmallows are melted.
Add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Add hot mixture slowly to cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Add pineapple and walnuts.
Chill until set.
Fold in whipped cream and mayonnaise.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into lightly oiled 2-quart mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Loosen edges; invert on serving plate.
Garnish with grapes and pineapple (sliced), if desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: speedy mustard sauce
directions: Just mix in blender or shaker and serve over your favorite fish.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar and cream well.
Blend in sour cream.
Sift together dry ingredients and blend well.
Chill. Roll out on floured board.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place pie crust into a 9-inch pie pan. With an electric mixer on medium speed, combine eggs, sugar, corn syrup, cocoa and butter. Pour into pie shell and bake for 45 minutes. Serve warm or cold. Makes 8 servings.

title: mein chicken
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Dice celery, onion and eggs and mix together with mayonnaise, soup, chicken and noodles.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cajun shrimp pasta
directions: Saute 3 cloves garlic in olive oil (about 1/4 cup).
Add seasonings.
Add tomatoes.
Cook over medium heat for about 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and beer.
Simmer until shrimp is cooked. Add butter (1 1/2 sticks) until melted.
Pour sauce over cooked pasta (may use rice instead).

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper in skillet.
Drain.
Mix cornbread mix, milk, egg and corn.
Set aside.
Butter a 10-inch baking dish.
Pour 1/2 of the cornbread mixture into dish.
Spread meat mixture and 1/2 of grated cheese.
Pour on remaining cornbread mixture and sprinkle the remaining cheese on the top. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Check it at about 40 minutes.
I used ovens that made it done by that time.

title: shrimp
directions: Arrange shrimp in a layer on bottom of glass baking dish. Microwave on full power until shell in pink, 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir once during cooking.

title: cocoa cherry drops
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large bowl.
Add egg and vanilla; blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chopped nuts and cherries.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Garnish with candied cherries or walnut pieces, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: turkey patties
directions: Blend all ingredients except oil.
Shape into 4 patties.
Heat oil in skillet.
Saute patties over medium heat for 5 minutes on each side or until cooked through.

title: whipped topping cappuccino
directions: Pour water into coffeemaker. Place frozen whipped topping into empty coffeepot. Brew coffee as normal. Serve immediately.

title: italian spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet until medium hot.
Add chopped onion and garlic to skillet and cook until glossy.
Add salt and pepper to meat and form into 2-inch balls.
Add to skillet.
Brown lightly.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Cover and cook on medium heat for 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook slowly until sauce thickens.
Serve over spaghetti which has been cooked until tender and drained.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into patties.
Fry in 1/2 cup oil until golden brown or preheat oven to 350°, then bake on both sides until golden brown (for 20 to 30 minutes).
Makes 8 cakes.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and lay in baking dish; lightly season with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Top with bacon; pour Catalina dressing over bacon. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes or until bacon is cooked thoroughly.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, using hand mixer.
Chill overnight. Serve with large Frito chips.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours in a buttered casserole dish.
Let sit a few minutes before cutting.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry lemon swirl pie
directions: Mash strawberries. In small saucepan combine sugar and cornstarch. Stir in mashed strawberries and water. Cook and stir until mixture thickens. Cook and stir 2 minutes more. Stir in lemon juice, margarine and food coloring. Cover with plastic wrap. Cool.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Add chopped chicken to chicken broth.
Add all other ingredients and cook until thick.

title: amber pettit's fruit cake
directions: Put nuts and fruit in a bowl.
Add dry ingredients and mix together.
Add beaten egg yolks, brandy and vanilla flavoring. Beat egg whites and fold into nut, dry ingredients and egg mixture. Bake for 1 hour in 300° oven.
Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Beat Ricotta cheese, eggs and parsley together.
Simmer the vegetables in Prego sauce for 10 minutes.
Layer in a 10 x 13-inch baking dish the sauce, noodles and Ricotta mix, repeating until all ingredients are used up, ending with sauce layer.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: piccardos
directions: Debone chicken and grind up.
Combine chicken, spices and salsa.
Place on corn tortilla.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.

title: apple stuffed pork loin
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter.
Add to dry bread cubes. Add apple pie filling.
If still too dry, add small amount of bouillon of chicken stock to moisten.
Stuff roast, skewer or tie closed.
Roast at 350°, uncovered, until done, about one hour or depending on size of roast.

title: shredded wheat bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix together and let cool:
shredded wheat biscuits, shortening, sugar, molasses, salt and boiling water. Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in the 1/2 cup lukewarm water. Stir into the above mixture.
Add about 6 cups flour. Mix well and turn onto a floured surface and
knead.
Let rise until double. Then make into two loaves of bread or 2 dozen rolls and place in greased pans.
Let rise again until doubled and bake at 375° for 30 minutes for bread or 20-25 minutes for rolls.

title: fruit squares
directions: Spread chopped nuts on bottom of greased and floured pan.
Mix softened butter, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and flour.
Pour over nuts.
Sprinkle chopped cherries over top of batter.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Cut into squares while warm.
Leave in pan to cool.

title: zucchini tart
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fit dough into a 9-inch tart pan.
Line shell by pressing a double thickness of aluminum foil against dough.
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove foil and bake until the edges brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Grate zucchini.
Toss with salt.
Beat eggs to mix and stir in milk.
Cream nutmeg and pepper.
Drain zucchini and blot with paper towels to remove excess moisture. Grate cheese and sprinkle half of it in tart shell.
Cover with zucchini.
Pour in milk and cream mixture and top with remaining cheese.
Bake until puffed and golden, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: just good (cherry dessert)
directions: Mix margarine, flour, sugar, nuts, and salt together. Bake in a 9x13 or two 8x2 pans at 375 for 15 minutes. Prepare 2 envelopes of dream whip according to directions. Then mix into the dream whip, the cream cheese and powdered sugar. Put on crust. Add cherry pie filling to top of pie. Refrigerate.

title: appetizer sauce
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Blend in catsup a small amount at a time until well mixed.

title: chocolate-raspberry pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 360°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan. In small microwave-safe bowl, place 3/4 cup preserves.
Microwave at High (100% power) for 30 to 45 seconds or until melted; cool. In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add butter, sour cream, eggs, vanilla and melted preserves. With electric mixer at medium speed, beat 3 to 4 minutes or until well blended.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes, or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan to wire rack.

title: surprise cake
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows on bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour batter over marshmallows.
Combine cherry pie filling and dry gelatin and spread over batter.
Bake at 350°.

title: great meat rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients (except bacon) together; form into 4 x 2-inch rolls.
Wrap with 1/2 strip of bacon each.
Bake in 350° oven for 1
hour.

title: microwave red rice
directions: Saute onions, shallots, parsley, bell pepper and sausage over stove a few minutes.
Add everything else except rice.
Let this come to a boil.
Now add rice.
Take this off of the stove.
Cover with lid.
Microwave for 35 minutes on 50% power.
Stir twice during cooking.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving (covered).
Do not over microwave.
This may not look done.
The longer it stands, the better it is.
It finishes cooking while standing.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: To slightly beaten eggs, add salt, spices, oleo, sugar and milk.
Add pumpkin.
Add flour with baking powder.
Stir only until moistened.
Line muffin tins with paper baking cups.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate-coated cherry surprise(candy)
directions: Combine in a bowl the creamy peanut butter, powdered sugar, unsalted butter and vanilla; set aside.
Chill in refrigerator. Drain cherries with stems; dry and set aside.
