Remove chilled ingredients in bowl.
Roll ingredients into medium size balls to go around cherries.
Flatten the balls put around cherries. Refrigerate until chilled.
Dip cherries in chocolate.

title: baked custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish that has been lined with a dark, golden-brown caramel coating.

title: caramel corn
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, syrup and butter.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat, add soda and salt.
Pour over corn.
Mix lightly and thoroughly.
In roaster or on large cookie sheet, bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: raw peach pie
directions: Mix together cornstarch and sugar.
Add 1 cup boiling water. Cook until cornstarch clears.
Add 1 box peach jello.
Take off heat.
Cool some, then add 2 cups sliced peaches.
Cool in refrigerator, then top with Cool Whip.

title: microwave fudge(microwave)
directions: Sift cocoa and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add milk and lay margarine sticks on the top.
Do not stir.
Cook on HIGH for 6 minutes.
Remove from the microwave and stir thoroughly.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour onto buttered platter.
Cool in the refrigerator for one hour.
Cut and serve.

title: quick chicken fajitas(4 servings)
directions: Heat oil in large, heavy skillet over medium-high heat.
Add onion and bell pepper; saute until almost tender, about 10 minutes.
Add cumin, paprika, cayenne, garlic powder, oregano and thyme; continue cooking 1 minute.
Mix in broth and bring to boil. Add chicken; stir until cooked through, about 5 minutes.
Spoon chicken mixture into tortillas.
Top with tomato and avocado. Roll up.
Serve, passing salsa separately.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients; blend well.
Cover in an airtight canister.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup.
Add hot water.

title: lemon broccoli chicken
directions: In skillet in hot 1 tablespoon oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned.
Combine soup and milk; stir in lemon juice and pepper.
Pour over chicken; reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until tender.
Serve with cooked broccoli.

title: saltine sweeties
directions: Melt butter and sugar together in saucepan.
Line jelly roll pan or cookie sheet with saltines.
Pour mixture over saltines. Bake in oven at 375° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with semi-sweet chocolate bits.
Return to oven for 1 minute. Remove from oven; spread out chocolate bits.
Sprinkle with finely chopped walnuts.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Break into brittle type pieces.

title: homemade french dressing
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients to taste.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix by hand.
Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain, flake and remove bones and skin from salmon.
Combine first 7 ingredients and mix well.
Chill several hours.
Shape into ball and roll in nuts and parsley.
You may wrap and freeze for later.
If salmon is too costly, 2 cans of tuna are just as yummy.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and bell pepper.
Drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients in crock-pot and cook on high for 3 hours.

title: mike's shrimp parmesan(serves 10)
directions: Place shrimp in baking dish.
Melt butter; pour over shrimp. Sprinkle with garlic powder, onion powder, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with marinara sauce.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes in 400° oven.
Enjoy!

title: green tomato relish
directions: Put through meat grinder:
green tomatoes, green pepper, red pepper and onions.
Drain off most of the juice.
Cook for about 30 minutes.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt, mustard seed and celery seed.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Pour into hot sterilized pint jars and seal.
Makes 3 to 4 pints.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place layer of chicken on bottom of baking dish.
Add sliced eggs.
Mix soup, broth and onion.
Pour over chicken and eggs. Mix flour, butter and milk.
Spoon over other ingredients.
Bake at 325° until brown, approximately 1 hour.

title: curried cream of broccoli soup
directions: In large saucepan melt butter or margarine; saute onion and garlic.
Add curry powder, pepper, chicken broth and water and bring soup to a boil.
Add broccoli, cut into flowerets, stems cut into 1/2 inch slices and potatoes cut into 1/2 inch cubes.
When mixture returns to a boil, reduce heat, cover pan and simmer soup for about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
You can puree soup in batches in blender or food processor or you can leave whole.
Stir in 1 cup milk and cook over low heat until hot.
Do not boil.

title: wisconsin chop suey(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Brown the ground beef and onions.
Combine with the remaining ingredients except the noodles in a casserole.
Bake, covered, for 1/2 hour at 375°.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add the other ingredients.
Stir well and put in crock-pot.
Cook 6 hours on high or 12 hours on low. Drain off excess broth.

title: crock-pot salsa
directions: Turn on crock-pot to high setting.
Cut into chunks, both cheeses, and place in the pot.
Add salsa and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover with a lid.

title: diet fruit salad
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip together with pudding.
Add fruit and/or nuts, if you wish.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
It's better if made one day prior to serving.

title: 7 seas casserole
directions: Combine water, soup, onion, salt and pepper in pan.
Bring to a slow boil.
Pour 1/3 of soup mixture into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Layer 1/3 of rice, peas and tuna.
Repeat 2 more times. Stir very gently.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Stir gently; cover and bake for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Cook noodles ahead; drain. Add soup to hamburger; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add in enough noodles to be creamy; simmer for 15 minutes.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mash artichokes lightly; stir in mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and garlic salt.
Bake in a small serving dish at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with an assortment of crackers.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: mom lane's buttermilk biscuits
directions: Add salt and baking powder to buttermilk and mix well. Add 2 cups flour to 1/3 cup soft butter and mix well.
Add 3 cups flour and mix well. Roll out on well floured flat surface.
Spread bacon grease in bottom of pan.
Cut biscuits by pressing top of drinking glass onto rolled out flour.
Lay and separate cut biscuits in bottom of pan.
Spread more bacon grease on top of each biscuit. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: instead of jam
directions: Soak fruit overnight to soften.
Liquify in blender with other ingredients.
Use in place of jam or butter.

title: hamburger tater tot
directions: Spray 9 x 9-inch pan lightly with Pam.
Pat hamburger in the bottom of the pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spread cream of mushroom soup on top of hamburger.
Layer Tater Tots on top of soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check middle to make sure hamburger is done.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: crispy parmesan potato wedges
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into quarters.
Mix flour, cheese, salt and pepper in bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake, a few at a time, in bag, coating well with cheese mixture.
Melt margarine in a 13 x
9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place potatoes in single layer in pan. Bake at 375° for about 1 hour, turning once.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil over medium heat.
Stir for 3 minutes after it begins to boil.
Remove from heat and add the rest of the ingredients.
Beat to cool.
Pour in buttered dish.
Let cool completely and cut in squares.

title: chill subcider
directions: In a small saucepan combine brown sugar, butter, almond extract and nutmeg until ingredients are smoothly blended.
Put into large pan or urn and add apple cider, pineapple juice and cranberry juice.
Heat until steaming, sipping hot!

title: baked vidalia onions
directions: Remove the stems from Vidalia onions.
Place each onion in a 9 x 11-inch shallow pan lined with aluminum foil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place a pat of butter on top of each with 1 beef bouillon cube, 3/4 cup boiling water, 1/4 teaspoon thyme, 3/4 cup fresh bread crumbs and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cracker snack
directions: Place all crackers and pretzels in a very large bowl. Sprinkle powdered Ranch dressing over and stir.
Then drizzle oil slowly over dry ingredients, while stirring with wooden spoon. Use entire bottle of oil.
Let mixture stand for several hours, then place in an airtight container and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Can be frozen.

title: diabetic punch bowl cake
directions: Stack in layers by order given.
Top with coconut and nuts. Chill.

title: teeny wienies
directions: Heat until melted jelly and mustard.
Add hot dogs.
Simmer. Enjoy!

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Note:
Substitution on cake flour is 1 cup plain flour minus 2 tablespoons.

title: rice krispies chewies
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup in a large saucepan; heat to boil. Stir.
Set off burner.
Add peanut butter and put back on burner. Stir constantly and bring to a boil; remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt chips together and pour over Rice Krispies treats.
Let cool, then cut into squares.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Roll or crush crackers, chip candy, chop nuts and cut marshmallows.
Cook cherries in 1 cup sugar slowly until candied. In a saucepan over low heat, cook marshmallows and milk, beating until marshmallows are melted.
Place dry ingredients in bowl. Pour cherries and marshmallow-milk mixture and mix well well. Press into tube pan and refrigerate.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Shape into ball and roll in finely chopped pecans.
Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and salt.
Add baking powder and eggs and mix well.
Add flour, milk and vanilla and mix well again.
Fold in blueberries.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease and flour 12 cup muffin pan.
Fill muffin cups to the top of the pan, then sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes, then drop temperature to 375° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: molded tuna salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water.
Drain and flake tuna. Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water; stir in softened gelatin. Add salt and cool.
Mix lemon juice, mayonnaise, tuna, celery, cucumber and pimento and add to gelatin mixture.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.
Makes 6 deliciously cool salads.

title: bread pudding with custard
directions: Scald milk and water in microwave.
Add stale broken up bread and smash with fingers.
Add 1 cup sugar and oleo.
Stir until well mixed.
Add beaten egg yolks with the other 1/2 cup sugar.
Add vanilla, raisins and pineapple.
Pour into buttered glass or baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or a little more.
Halfway through baking, stir bread pudding from the center to the outer edge of the pan.
When finished baking, take out of oven and let cool a few minutes.
Put custard on top of pudding and then add your meringue.
Put back into oven at 300° for 10 minutes or until meringue is lightly brown.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 20.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Wash the zucchini and leave on counter overnight, making sure they are really ripe.
Mix the first 7 ingredients together on high speed.
Batter gets thick.
Take zucchini and add to batter by hand; turns liquidy.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Check with toothpick in center for doneness. Outside will look done long before inside is.
Makes 2 bread pan loaves or 1 Bundt pan.

title: mayonnaise muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Drop into a well-greased muffin pan.
Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: amaretto sour cream cake(serves 16)
directions: Using 2 tablespoons shortening, generously grease a 10-inch tube pan; set aside.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Blend together sugar, butter, Crisco and egg.
Set aside. Blend together in separate bowl, the flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to sugar, butter, Crisco and egg mixture. Blend well.
Add applesauce, cloves and cinnamon.
Blend well. Fold in raisins and nuts if wanted.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: candy bar dessert
directions: Cut up candy bars into small pieces.
Slice bananas into small pieces.
Crush the peppermint stick.
Mix in a large glass bowl or dish into individual dessert dishes.
Chill and serve.
Serves about eight 1 cup servings.

title: glazed carrots 'n apples
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1-quart casserole.
Cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir and continue cooking on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until carrots are tender-crisp.
Let stand, covered, 3 minutes before serving. Serves 5 to 6.

title: sweet potato dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook beef and 1/2 cup onions until meat is brown and onions are tender. Drain fat. Add chili powder. Cook and stir 1 minute. Stir in 1 can enchilada sauce, garlic salt and pepper. Simmer meat mixture, covered, for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: fat-free carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 8 jumbo muffin pan cups with Pam. Place muffin pan on jelly roll pan for easier handling.

title: corned beef mold
directions: Melt jello in hot water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put into bowl or mold and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
May be frozen.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip until smooth. Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Spread pie filling on top. Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken with mustard sauce
directions: In a large skillet, cook chicken breasts in butter or margarine until tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Remove chicken to warm platter.
Stir flour into skillet drippings.
Add chicken broth and light cream.
Cook until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir in mustard.
Add chicken.
Cover and heat 10 minutes.
Serve over rice and garnish with tomatoes and parsley.
Serves four.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well. Chill. Serve with your vegetables.

title: children
directions: Mix children with dogs, blend with sunshine, empty into field, and stir continuously.
Pour brook gently over pebbles.
Sprinkle field with flowers.
Cover all with a deep blue sky and bake in the hot sun.
When children are well browned, call them home.
Will be found ready to take from the oven and cool in bathtub.
Delicious when served with hugs and kisses.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook peppers about 5 minutes in salt water.
Boil macaroni in salt water for 5 to 10 minutes.
Saute onions and brown hamburger in onions.
Add macaroni, tomato sauce, ketchup, salt and pepper.

title: quick and easy baked beans(vegetarian)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in margarine until transparent, about 4 minutes.
Combine all ingredients and place in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, 45 to 60 minutes. Yield:
24 servings.
Approximate calories per serving:

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice until tender and set aside.
Mix flour or cornstarch with sugar and salt.
Separate eggs and set whites aside.
Beat yolks with fork and mix with milk.
Stir in sugar mixture and cook over medium heat until boiling.
Boil while stirring for 1 minute. Stir in butter and vanilla.
Stir in rice and raisins.
Use the egg whites to make meringue.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Place first four ingredients in skillet and cook until dates have dissolved, letting it boil a little and stirring constantly. Remove from stove.
Add 1 cup pecans, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup Rice Krispies cereal.
(Add more cereal if needed.)
Cool.
Roll in balls, then in fine coconut.
Makes delicious candy-like cookies.

title: chop suey
directions: Cook meat with crisco until brown on all sides.
Add water, onion, celery, brown sugar.
Cook until tender, add mushrooms, and bean sprouts.
Take cornstarch, add soy sauce until thick mixture. Take 1 cup of hot meat broth and add to cornstarch.
Slowly add cornstarch mixture to pan with meat and vegetables.
Stirring constantly.
(Meat mixture must be hot and bubbling before cornstarch can be added.)
This will become thick and make a nice gravy over the meat and vegetables.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding mix in Pet milk until thick.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 container of Cool Whip. Layer pudding mix in large bowl with vanilla wafers and bananas. Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate to set.
Drizzle chocolate syrup on top before serving.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Bring water to boil and add grits slowly.
Cook 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Add butter, cheese, beaten eggs and Tabasco sauce.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Cover with corn flakes.
Bake for 40 minutes at 400°.

title: *grandmother's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream oil, butter, sugars and peanut butter.
Add eggs and milk and blend well with spoon.
Add baking soda and salt to flour.
Mix well with creamed ingredients.
Roll into balls (about a teaspoon each).
Place on well-greased cookie sheets, about 2 inches apart, and press with fork.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 9 minutes.

title: green beans in mustard sauce
directions: Cook beans in salted water 5 to 8 minutes, until crisp-tender. Drain.
In a bowl, whisk together remaining ingredients and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add beans and toss.
Serve hot or cold.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Put pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over the top.
Pour melted butter over top of cake mix.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake according to directions on cake box for 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: carrot nut bread
directions: Mix (do not beat), eggs, sugar and carrots.
Add oil slowly, otherwise oil settles to the top.
Add dry ingredients all at once; mix.
Mixture is heavy.
Add nuts.
Use 5 x 9-inch pan, line the bottom.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test before removing from oven. Let bread cool; loosen edges, remove from pan, and wrap in foil while still warm.
Place in refrigerator to cool (makes it moist).

title: russian (spice) tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and keep in airtight container.
Use 2 heaping spoonfuls to each cup of boiling water.

title: congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Add enough water to juice to make one cup; bring to a boil.
Add jello and cream cheese; beat with beater until smooth.
Set aside to cool, then fold in Cool Whip, carrot and pineapple.
Pour into a square dish to chill.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce.

title: bran muffins--frugal way
directions: Dissolve the baking soda in 2 cups of boiling water (microwave).
Set aside to cool.

title: waverly wafer cookies
directions: Spread crackers on sprayed baking sheet (on large or two medium).
Cook butter, margarine and sugar to a soft ball stage. Add nuts and vanilla or almond.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 250° to 300° until brown.

title: mushroom muffins
directions: Fry mushrooms lightly in 2 teaspoons of butter.
Drain.
Sift dry ingredients and mix in Cheddar cheese.
In a bowl, mix together the beaten egg, melted butter, milk and mushrooms.
Add dry ingredients to the liquid mixture.
Pour into muffin pan and bake in oven for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Serve warm with salad or soup.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients and beat for 30 seconds.
Pour into a lightly greased round pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: crispy baked fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Wash and dry fillets; cut into serving pieces.
Season, dip in oil and coat with cornflake crumbs. Arrange in a single layer in a lightly oiled, shallow baking dish. Bake for 10 minutes without turning or basting.
(This method produces a crisp coating; looks almost like deep fried fish.) Yields 4 servings.

title: artichoke cheese nibbles
directions: Drain marinade from 1 jar of artichokes into skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Combine eggs, spices, crumbs and chopped artichokes.
Fold all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9-inch square dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into small squares and serve warm.
This can be precooked and reheated.

title: hamburger-steak sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Brush on both sides of hamburgers or steaks; let stand 15 minutes.
During cooking, brush meat with sauce.
Makes about 2/3 cup.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Make hole in flour; add yeast, then buttermilk.
Mix well. Cover bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Roll; cut and let rise about 2 hours.
Dough will keep for a week.

title: brown sugar squares
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Stir together egg, brown sugar and vanilla.
Quickly stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Add nuts; spread in pan and bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes. (Should be soft in center when taken from oven.)
Cool in pan; cut into squares.

title: end of the garden pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, peppers, cabbage, onions, celery and tomatoes in salt water overnight (1/2 cup salt to 2 quarts water).
Drain. Cook the carrots and string beans in boiling water until tender; drain water.
Mix soaked and cooked vegetables with remaining ingredients and boil for 10 minutes.
Place in sterilized jars; seal at once.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish.
Place one slice onion and 1 teaspoon rice on each chop.
Pour tomatoes over the top.
Bake at 350° for 90 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together and let stand overnight in refrigerator. Bake until heated through at 350°.
Makes 2 casseroles (one or both can be frozen for later).

title: apricot salad or dessert
directions: Combine jello, water and juice from apricots and pineapple. Mix until dissolved.
Add mashed apricots and pineapple (crushed). Sprinkle marshmallows on top.
Chill until stiff.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles.
Saute until tender the celery, green pepper and onion.
Heat and add the soup, milk and cheese; stir until melted.
Add cubed turkey or chicken and drained pineapple cubes. Top with bread crumbs or potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake the sugar cookie dough in a pizza pan style.

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir twice for most even cooking.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Combine caramels and 1/2 Eagle Brand milk; melt completely. Combine remainder of milk, dry cake mix and melted butter. Press 1/2 dough mixture into loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Pour caramel mixture over baked mixture. Pour 1/2 of the chopped pecans and 1/2 the chocolate chips on top. Take remainder of dough and pat into cookies. Place the patted cookies on top of loaf pan mixture. Sprinkle with remainder of nuts and chips. Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: yummy berry salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, poppy seeds and milk to make dressing.
Set aside.
Tear lettuce in bite size pieces; add strawberries and onions.
Pour dressing on when ready to serve. Toss well.
Makes 14 to 16 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt oleo and add to crackers.
Put this on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (uncovered).

title: raspberry vinaigrette dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well in mixer or food processor.
Mix until mixture thickens and is blended well.

title: cold marinated carrots
directions: Combine soup, oil, vinegar, and sugar and bring to boil. Add onions, peppers and worcestershire sauce.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Make the pastry and line a 9-inch pie plate.
Combine the flour, cornstarch, salt and sugar.
Add the rind and lemon juice, milk and beaten egg yolks.
Mix the ingredients very well, then fold in 3 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Beat remaining egg white slightly and spread over the inside of the unbaked pastry crust. Pour filling into pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: k's ham delights
directions: Process ham, cheese and onion in blender separately.
Add remaining ingredients.
Split rolls.
Fill with mixture.
Wrap in tinfoil.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Do not let burn.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 bread tins. Mix all ingredients in bowl on medium for 2 minutes.
Pour into tins. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, until tops are light brown.
Cool for 10 minutes, then remove from tins.

title: chicken and rice deluxe
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Drain beans.
Combine all ingredients and place in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes. Top with grated cheese and cook 5 more minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: praline rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Into dry ingredients stir milk which has been cooled to lukewarm.
Add egg into yeast and water mixture. Beat well.
Turn onto floured surface and roll until 10 x 15-inches.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Spread over dough; sprinkle with nuts.
Roll up, starting at 15-inch side; cut into 1-inch slices, then place on greased sheet and flatten.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy party punch
directions: Combine kool-aid, sugar and water.
Add pineapple juice.
Put in ice cubes, then add ginger ale.
Serve at once.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and toss well.
Chill. (Cool pasta under cold water before adding other ingredients.)
Serves 8 to 10. Good with any kind of meat.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Debone chicken and mix well with other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain well.
Line a buttered casserole dish with crescent rolls.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Cover with sausage.
Add cheese to cover.
Combine eggs, milk and salt. Pour over sausage and cheese mixture.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: pea salad
directions: In a clear baking dish, spread your chopped lettuce, then your chopped onions, celery, chestnuts and then your peas.
Spread mayo evenly on top.
Last use cheese and thinly sliced or chopped tomatoes.
Cover with Saran Wrap for 24 hours.
Then serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for one hour. After first 30 minutes, top with corn flake crumbs.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Sift together all the dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk to dry mixture.
Refrigerate until dough is cold.
Knead enough to hold together and roll 1/2 to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter, dip in melted butter and fold.
Pat tops of folded rolls with melted butter.
Let rise 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 450° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen (may be refrigerated or frozen before baking).

title: cranberry apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
In large bowl stir together sugars, flour and cinnamon.
Add apples and cranberries. Mix to coat well.
Turn into pastry-lined pie pan.
Pat with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Cut slits in crust.
Seal and flute edges. Bake 40 to 50 minutes; cool.

title: dot chocolates
directions: Melt chips in top of double boiler.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Take up and store in candy tin or airtight container.

title: nacho dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except for Nacho chips and simmer on stove for 1 hour or in crock pot on low for 2 hours.

title: garlic grits casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a casserole dish (8 x 8-inch). Cook grits in boiling salted water according to directions on package.
Add margarine and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add the beaten eggs with the milk.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into prepared casserole.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes until nicely browned on top.
Serve piping hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Layer
carrots	and
cheese in buttered casserole dish. Saute onion
in
one stick of butter or margarine.
Pour over carrots and
cheese.
Top
with crushed Ritz crackers.
Dot a little butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramels
directions: Grease	8-inch square baking pan.
Combine all ingredients
in large
saucepan.
Cook
over low heat, stirring constantly, until
sugars
are dissolved.
Bring to a boil; boil without stirring,
to firm ball stage.
Pour into pan;
cool. Cut in 1-inch squares.
Wrap in wax paper.

title: clam dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together well.
Serve with your favorite dippers.

title: grandmother's cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until well blended.
Add egg and mix
well.
Stir
in flour.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet. Flatten
with
fork dipped in cold water (horizontally and vertically).
Bake
at
for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges brown.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
At the same time, also make the macaroni and cheese following manufacturer's instructions.
In a casserole pan, put a layer of macaroni and cheese (1/3 of the macaroni and cheese), then 1/2 of the beef, then spread 1/2 can cream of celery soup.
Finish the casserole by placing layers of macaroni and cheese, meat, soup and finally, the rest of the macaroni and cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: kiwi pie
directions: Mix sugar, cream cheese, pineapple, coconut and Cool Whip together. Set aside.

title: baked omelet
directions: Spread croutons in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cheese over croutons.
Brown the sausage.
Drain and put over cheese and croutons.
Combine the soup, milk, eggs, dry mustard and onion.
Beat together.
Pour over croutons, cheese and sausage.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender. Blend on low speed 1 minute or until smooth.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Makes 1 cup.

title: dulaney's favorite casserole(squash casserole)
directions: Slice squash (do not peel).
Add chopped onions and boil in saltwater until tender.
Drain.
In casserole dish, combine cream of chicken soup, sour cream, water chestnuts and shredded cheese. Mix Stove Top stuffing with 1 stick of butter and add 1/2 to the mixture.
Mix in squash and onions.
Top with remaining Stove Top stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon into greased casserole pan.
Slice eggs on top; top with bread or cracker crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until bubbly.
Almonds are optional.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Cook hamburg and drain.
Set aside in a large bowl.
Cut up Spam and Velveeta cheese in small squares.
Mix with hamburg.
Add spices, spaghetti sauce and parsley.
Mix all ingredients well. Spread on one half hamburger buns; place on cookie sheet and bake at 450° until cheese melts or about 10 minutes.
You may freeze or refrigerate.

title: quick and easy rice dressing casserole
directions: Brown ground meat in Crisco.
Add celery and bell pepper; cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat; pour in greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dump bars
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs, oil, vanilla, salt, pecans, and cocoa.
Pour in greased 9x13 pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips. Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Mix all ingredients well in large pan.
Pour into tube cake pan.
Put in refrigerator for a few days.

title: b-52
directions: Layer each ingredient in a small bar glass.
This drink is good for shots or sipping!

title: cheesy picnic potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine 1 1/2 cups cheese, soup, milk, barbecue sauce, oregano, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Stir in potatoes until well coated.
Put into a shallow buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and paprika.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Combine flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, oleo, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Mix until mixture is as fine as cornmeal.
Spread over bottom and halfway up sides of an ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan. Place peaches on dough (cut side up).
Combine cinnamon and 1 cup sugar.
Sprinkle on peaches.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Mix eggs and cream.
Pour over peaches and bake 30 minutes.

title: cucumber vinaigrette
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and chill for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: louisiana fruit salad
directions: Mix everything together and chill.
This keeps under refrigeration up to 2 weeks in a sealed container.
The bananas do not turn dark.

title: taco pie
directions: Spread crescent rolls in casserole dish.
Brown meat and onion in skillet; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning, tomato sauce and water.
Spread meat mixture over dough and then spread sour cream over meat.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top and add crushed tortilla chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon jell-o cake
directions: Fold eggs into cake mix one at a time.
Meanwhile, dissolve Jell-O with the boiling water.
Set aside to cool while making batter.
Add oil and extract to cake/egg batter;
mix well.
Add cooled Jell-O and mix.
Spray a tube or Bundt pan.
Pour in batter and bake at 300° for 60-65 minutes.
Let cool 5-10 minutes.

title: jon's broccoli
directions: In deep saucepan, put salad dressing and fresh garlic (let simmer).
Don't burn the garlic!
Add broccoli to pan and squeeze fresh lemon on the broccoli.
Put cover on the pan and let broccoli simmer, stirring occasionally.
Cook broccoli to your liking.

title: slow cooker stew
directions: Coat
meat
in flour.
Add soup, soup mix and catsup in slow cooker;
mix well.	Add meat and stir.
Cook all day, at least
8 hours.
Add can of mixed vegetables.
Heat another 15 minutes. Serve with rice and/or bread.

title: corn salad
directions: Pour corn in bowl and stir; then add finely diced onions, bell pepper and celery.
Salt and pepper.
Mix in diced tomato.
Add mayonnaise to taste or liking.
Chill and serve as a vegetable. May want to triple recipe for large group.

title: fried cabbage
directions: In heavy skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet; leave drippings.
Add remaining ingredients to skillet. Cover and cook over medium heat until tender and slightly brown, stirring often, approximately 20 minutes.
Pour into serving dish and garnish with crumbled up bacon.
Delightfully tasty.

title: sliced cucumbers vinaigrette
directions: At least 4 1/2 hours before serving, cut cucumbers into 1/4-inch slices.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, measure vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and seasoning.
Stir to mix well.
Add cucumbers, turning to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours.

title: bran muffins(refrigerated batter)
directions: Beat the buttermilk, oil and eggs until blended.
Add the dry ingredients and mix, stirring only until moist.
This batter will keep for up to 6 weeks in the refrigerator.
It makes 2 dozen muffins.
Bake them at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Grease a baking dish.
Combine all ingredients, mixing until zucchini is just coated with batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: black forest dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling over bottom of 2-quart glass casserole dish.
Add chocolate chips evenly over top.
Add dry cake mix evenly.
Slice oleo and dot evenly over top.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: corn beef hash and potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough water to
keep it from sticking.
Cook until potatoes are done.

title: shrimp and rice(serves 4)
directions: Using medium size frypan, saute rice in oil until rice turns white.
Add water and bouillon cubes and cover.
Cook over low heat until water evaporates and rice is cooked.
(Do not stir or overcook rice.)
In separate pan, saute butter, wine, seasonings and shrimp.
Cook shrimp until slightly firm, then remove just shrimp from pan.
In remaining juice, cook mushrooms and scallions until tender.
Return shrimp to pan and simmer until shrimp is completely cooked.
When rice is done, combine rice and shrimp mixture together and serve.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Bring
the sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk to a rolling boil. In mixing bowl, have ready oatmeal and nuts.
Add vanilla to hot mixture and then add it to the oatmeal mixture.
Mix well and spoon quickly on wax paper.

title: burger bundles
directions: Make large hamburg patty.
Place on large piece of heavy foil. Slice vegetables fairly thin.
Place around meat.
Season with salt, pepper, onion powder, etc.
Wrap tightly.
Place on grill, turn several times.
Cooks in about 1/2 hour.
Open and serve in foil.

title: taco crockpot soup
directions: Combine all ingredients into crock pot and cook four to six hours.
No need to brown beef.
Top with shredded cheese and fritos.

title: chocolate nut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in a double boiler.
Add peanuts.
Stir.
Remove from heat.
Drop by spoonfuls upon waxed paper.
Let cool. Yields 40 to 50 clusters.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Beat well at medium speed about 2 minutes.
Pour into Bundt pan which has been sprayed well with vegetable spray or greased and floured well.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° until done by toothpick test.
Cool and glaze with 1 cup powdered sugar and 1/4 cup blackberry wine.
Barely bring to boil.
Punch holes in cake and pour glaze over cake.
If you boil the glaze, it will crystallize.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients (including juice from artichoke can) in an oven-safe dish.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown. Serve with crackers.

title: supreme bean salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl; set aside. Combine vinegar, oil, salt and pepper in a small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar substitute.
Pour over vegetables; toss gently.
Cover and chill 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain before serving. Yields 7 servings.

title: egg estrata
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain.
Place in shallow dish.
In same pan, saute potatoes in butter until brown.
Place potatoes over sausage.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350° until done.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into a loaf pan lined with wax paper.
Bake for 35 minutes in a moderately slow oven (325° to 350°).
The cake can be served plain or covered with frosting.

title: low country shrimp boil
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Cook at a rolling boil for 15 minutes.
Lower to a medium boil; add sausage.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes; then add corn and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Bring back to a rolling boil.
Add shrimp.
Cook 1 to 3 minutes.
Drain and serve. Serves 2.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, cheese and Bisquick together.
Roll into small balls.
Place on a baking sheet and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla. Add egg; beat thoroughly. Stir in peanut butter. Sift dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture. Form into tiny balls on ungreased sheet. Press with fork to make crisscross. Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in mixer.
Add the fruit.
Put in an ice cream container; fill to line with milk.

title: caramel chocolate squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt together 1/4 cup evaporated milk and caramels.
Keep warm over low heat.
Mix dry cake mix with remaining milk, melted margarine and nuts.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate chips and coconut on baked cake mix.
Drizzle melted caramel mixture over top.
Drop remaining cake mixture randomly in small amounts over caramel drizzle.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool. Refrigerate until firm and cut into squares.

title: thin round molasses cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Make into little round balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass.
Best when quite thin; watch carefully as they burn easily.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: green spinach (broccoli) pie
directions: Thaw and drain spinach or broccoli.
Grate Cheddar cheese. Mix Cheddar cheese with thawed spinach or broccoli and cottage cheese.
In another bowl, mix eggs, flour, salt and pepper. Combine the two mixtures in one bowl and mix well.
Grease 9-inch square baking dish with butter; pour mixture evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Cool for several minutes before cutting.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and arrange in greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken on top.
Combine next 3 ingredients (soup, mayo and lemon juice).
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until heated.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: basic white cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in
mixing
bowl.
Add
shortening, 2/3 cup milk and flavoring.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add
1/3 cup milk and egg whites. Beat 2 more minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or so.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to directions and drain.
Place spinach and eggs in a shallow casserole dish and toss together.
Fry bacon, crumble and sprinkle over spinach.
Reserve 3 tablespoons bacon grease and saute onions in it until tender.
Drain and layer over spinach and bacon.
Mix together sour cream and grated cheese.
Spread over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: meat loaf (2)
directions: Mix above ingredients.	Put into greased loaf pan.
Pour catsup over top for taste.	Bake 1 hour, or more, at 350°, until done.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: Boil and debone 1 chicken.
Reserve 4 cups chicken broth. Saute onion and garlic.
Add to chicken and broth.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cheese hash browns
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Add hash browns and put into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with corn flakes and drizzle melted margarine over the top of corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: twist and shout cranberry jell-o salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Then add can of cranberry sauce to hot mixture and stir to break up/dissolve it, also.
Add drained, chopped oranges, celery and nuts.
Pour into large 9 x 13 Pyrex pan and refrigerate until it congeals.

title: spanish rice(sopa de arroz)
directions: Heat oil until sizzling hot.
Add rice and cook until deep brown, stirring constantly to prevent burning.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Cover and reduce heat to medium; do not open or stir for 20 minutes.
After time is up, let set for 15 additional minutes before serving.
Serves 10.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Sift and add flour, salt and soda.
Add oatmeal and nuts.
Mix well.
Shape into rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill approximately 30 minutes.
Slice 1/4-inch thick and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: blue moon drink
directions: Combine food coloring, cream of coconut, lemonade and extracts.
While mixture is blending, drop a couple of ice cubes at a time into swirling mixture until it becomes icy and frothy. Pour into glasses and put an orange slice on the side of each glass.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix
sugar,
vinegar,
cornstarch
and butter together. Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over prepared beets in saucepan and let stand
for	30
minutes.
If not warm enough, they may be heated on	low
for
a
few minutes before serving.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: pearl's beans
directions: Pour half the beans in a Dutch oven.
Mix brown sugar and mustard. Cover beans with half the mixture, then add remaining beans and cover with remaining mixture. Top with ketchup. Decorate with bacon. Bake 2 1/2 hours at 325°, uncovered.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pistachio pudding with pineapple and juice.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Put in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.

title: white chili
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain. Combine beans, broth, half the onion, garlic and salt in a large kettle. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or longer until beans are very tender.
Add more broth as needed. Heat oil in skillet.
Add remaining onion and cook until tender. Add chiles and spices.
Mix thoroughly. Cook about 20 minutes. Add skillet mixture to bean mixture. Stir in cooked chicken and heat through. Top with grated cheese.

title: harvard beets
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and blend.
Add water.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs first.
Add all other ingredients except buttermilk. Blend well.
Add buttermilk last.
Blend and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mash salmon; add horseradish, onion and lemon juice.
Add enough mayonnaise or sour cream for spreading consistency.
Serve with crackers or toast rounds.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles until tender.
Drain and place in large bowl. Heat cream of celery soup over medium heat with 1 1/2 cups water for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add tuna.
Mix until blended.
Pour over noodles and mix well.
Pour in large casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with dinner rolls or garlic cheese bread.

title: easy cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage and place in ungreased casserole dish.
Brown turkey and onion together.
Add rice and salt to turkey and onion mixture.
Pour all over cabbage in dish.
Stir.
Add tomatoes (with liquid).
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries, pineapple and pecans.
Halve mixture, putting half in pan and leaving other half in bowl.
Put pan in refrigerator and let gel.
After jelled, spread with sour cream.
Pour remaining half on top and let it gel.

title: walnut hermits
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to cream mixture, alternating with sour milk.
Add nuts and fruit.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: asparagus provencale
directions: Melt butter in a small saucepan; spoon off the white foam that rises to the surface to clarify the butter.
Cook slowly to a deep golden brown.
Snap the asparagus and peel the lower part of each spear with a vegetable peeler or small sharp knife.
Place the asparagus in a 10 to 12-inch skillet or saute pan.
Add water to barely cover it and sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Gently boil the asparagus, uncovered, until it is tender-crisp when pierced with the tip of a small sharp knife, about 5 minutes.
Drain and refresh the asparagus under cold water.
Drain the spears on paper towels and dry them thoroughly.

title: italian chews
directions: Cream butter. Add white sugar and beat until light. Add flour. Mix well. Pat into 13 x 2 inch pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Beat egg yolks. Gradually beat in brown sugar. Add nuts and coconut. Fold in egg whites. Bake 24 to 30 minutes. Cut in 54 squares and dust with confectioners sugar. Store in a tight place.

title: favorite hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add onions, buttermilk and eggs.
Cook in hot grease.

title: dipping mustard
directions: Mix in bowl all dry ingredients, add vinegar slowly and mix. Store covered in the refrigerator and be sure to stir it once a day for approximately 1 week. Mark your calendar so you don't forget.

title: layered cherry delight
directions: Line 9-inch square cake pan with graham crackers.
Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Let set for 5 minutes, then blend in Cool Whip.
Spread half of pudding mix over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers and top with remaining pudding mixture.
Cover with remaining pudding mixture.
Cover with remaining crackers.
Spread pie filling over the top.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: sausage pizza bake
directions: *May use other meat choice as desired.
Precooked meats such as smoked sausage can be used without browning.

title: baked potato and onion pie
directions: In a buttered oblong baking dish, place 1/3 of the potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle with salt.
Dot with 1/3 of the lemon juice. Repeat twice.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter and toss with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Top with paprika, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking until top is lightly browned.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: scott's favorite broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli and chop tips into fine pieces.
Combine with remaining ingredients, except stuffing mix.
Place in a round, glass casserole dish (about 9 x 9-inch).
Sprinkle the top with dry stuffing mix.

title: whisky icebox cake
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water. Then add boiling water and dissolve; set aside. In another bowl, beat egg yolks until thick. Add whisky very slowly. Beat in the sugar; add lemon juice. Stir in dissolved gelatin and chill a short time. Whip cream and fold it in mixture. Beat egg whites and fold in mixture. Line sides and bottom of a spring form pan (about 12-inches) with split lady fingers. Put the mixture in slowly. When about half way, put in layer of lady fingers. Then, when filled, place a layer of lady fingers on top in a design. Chill overnight in the refrigerator. Serves 12.

title: scalloped eggs with ham
directions: Blend the butter and flour together into a saucepan and cook until the butter is melted.
Add the milk a little at a time and cook the mixture until it boils.
Do not let it get too thick. Grease a baking dish and put a little of the sauce in the bottom, a layer of sliced eggs, a layer of the chopped ham.
Then more sauce, eggs and ham until the dish is filled.
Cover the top with buttered crumbs and bake until the sauce is thickened.

title: chicken breast in tomato cream sauce
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
In large frying pan, melt butter. Cook chicken until tender, 3 to 5 minutes on each side.
Remove and keep warm.
Add shallots to pan and cook until soft.
Add tomatoes; cook 2 minutes.
Add vermouth and boil 5 minutes until sauce thickens.
Pour sauce into food processor and puree until smooth.
Return to pan.
Add cream, simmer 2 minutes.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve.
Serve with thin noodles.

title: bergen meatballs
directions: A delicious and inexpensive Greek classic!

title: sausage soup
directions: Cut sausage in small pieces and saute in a large pot.
Add onions and peppers and saute.
Add broth and sherry.
Bring to a boil.
Add parsley, basil, oregano, garlic and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
If too thick, add a little water.
Add bows and cook until they are done, about 20 minutes.
Sprinkle each portion with Parmesan cheese.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine and pour into a hot greased frying pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Melt stick of margarine and pour over top after cutting cooked cornbread.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions and garlic in 6 tablespoons of butter until soft, but not brown.
Sprinkle with flour.
Add 1 can of soup and 1 can of water.
Bring to a boil.
Add remaining soup and water.
Add brandy just before serving.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place frozen dinner rolls in Bundt pan.
Pour melted margarine over rolls.
Sprinkle dill weed over rolls.
Cover pan and set out on counter to thaw and rise overnight.
Approximately 30 minutes before serving, bake rolls at 325° for about 20 to 25 minutes. Remove from oven and immediately turn Bundt pan upside down over serving dish.
Let Bundt pan stand upside down for about 5 minutes.
Remove Bundt pan and serve.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Use in amounts of 1 1/2 teaspoons per cup boiling water or 3 teaspoons per large mug in hot or boiling water.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Let stand few minutes and let oats absorb some of moisture.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Loosen cookies with spatula and let stand until cool on cookie sheet.

title: sour cream corn muffins
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased muffin tins and bake at 425° for about 15 minutes until lightly golden.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.
Use radishes, celery and carrot sticks and cauliflower for dipping.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Spray square casserole dish with nonstick spray.
Brown meat in a heavy, hot skillet to seal in juices.
Mix water, butter, milk and package of sauce mix from box in the dish.
Add in the potatoes and stir.
Arrange the chops or chicken on top and bake in a 400 degree oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in slow oven at 300° until crust is brown and filling is firm, about 1 hour.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in square baking pan.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add soda to sour milk. Sift flour and spices.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Alternate flour and milk; beat until mixture is smooth.
Fold in jam and floured raisins.
Bake in three 8-inch layer pans at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil water.
Add noodles.
Boil rapidly (stir often).
Cook until tender.
Drain water.
Add butter, milk and cheese sauce. Mix well.
Serve hot.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together; roll out.
Place in pie tins; freeze.
Makes 3 or 4 pie crusts.

title: layered salad
directions: Using glass bowl,
layer lettuce, bell pepper, green onions, and english peas.
Coat
with mayonnaise and completely seal with thick layer.
Refrigerate 8-24 hours.

title: pizza pie
directions: Mix all together and put in pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon angel trifle
directions: Break angel cake into walnut size pieces and put in a bowl. Sprinkle gelatin over water in bowl.
In top of double boiler, mix lemon juice with 1/2 cup sugar, egg yolks and lemon rind.
Stir and cook over hot water until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in gelatin mixture.
Set aside to cool.
Beat egg whites until foamy. Gradually beat in 1/2 cup of sugar, until mixture is stiff.
Fold into yolk mixture.
Beat 1 cup of cream until stiff and fold into yolk mixture.
Fold mixture into cake pieces.

title: margaret's meat loaf
directions: Combine oats, 1/2 cup ketchup, 1/8 cup sugar, hamburger, salt, diced pepper, pepper and onion in large mixing bowl.
Put in casserole dish.
Spread rest of ketchup and sugar on top.
Put into oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: quick dumplings and chicken
directions: Bring soup and water to rolling boil.
Mix biscuit mix, milk and poultry seasoning together.
Drop into boiling soup. Add chicken. Cook over low to medium heat 6 to 9 minutes. Real quick!

title: mozzarella and tomato crustini
directions: Brush tomatoes with olive oil, then sprinkle with salt, pepper, oregano and basil.
Let set several hours.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Cream pulp, eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift in dry ingredients and add milk and vanilla.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato-pineapple cake
directions: Mix everything in a 9-inch pan.
Melt 1 stick butter; remove from heat.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with cream.

title: christmas divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and corn syrup in heavy saucepan.
Cook, stirring, to hard ball stage.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; beat in gelatin.
Pour syrup over egg whites in thin stream, beating constantly.
Beat until candy is stiff and glossy; stir in nuts.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Pat dough out on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese and marshmallow cream together and spread on cool cookie dough.
Top with fresh fruit.

title: noodles and cabbage
directions: Saute chopped onion in margarine.
Add chopped cabbage, caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Cook until golden.
Cook noodles in boiling water 5 minutes.
Drain and add to cabbage.
Toss and blend.
Serve with sour cream, if desired.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Combine soups, Cheez Whiz, chicken broth and milk in a large microwave-safe bowl.
Mix and heat on High for 3 minutes; stir and heat for 3 more minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Stir, then add cooked spaghetti and chicken.
Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until set.

title: wassail
directions: Pour apple cider and ginger ale into bottom of a large electric coffee maker.
In top of basket, combine red hots, cinnamon sticks and cloves.
Perk until ready.

title: eggplant caesar
directions: Soak eggplant slices in cold water 15 or 20 minutes. Drain and blot dry. Spread lightly on both sides with mayonnaise, then press lightly into grated cheese, then into crumbs, lightly coating both sides. Spray shallow baking pan with cooking spray for no-fat frying. Arrange eggplant in single layer. Bake in pre-heated oven at 475° for five minutes. Turn and bake an additional three or four minutes until eggplant is golden and crisp on the outside and tender inside.

title: coconut cranberry bars
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter.
Press into 9 x 13 greased pan.
In bowl, combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spread over crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.

title: scombeli bread
directions: Roll out thawed bread dough to about 9 x 13-inches.
Mix eggs, spices and oil.
Spread on both loaves, reserving a small amount. Layer pepperoni, sausage, ham and cheese on dough in middle.
Roll up loaves, long side, jelly roll style.
Tuck in ends.
Put seam side down on cookie sheet.
Brush remaining egg mixture on top of loaves.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight or for several hours.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until done; drain the water off macaroni.
Put into mixing bowl.
Beat eggs well.
Blend fast with macaroni, making sure the eggs don't cook while stirring.
This is just a glaze.
Set aside.
Add pepper.
Melt all cheeses, milk and butter together.
Add to macaroni.
Place into a large baking dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown on top.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients, then fold in oysters.
Crumble a few crackers over top for a thin crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cherry kucha
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender.
Set aside 1 cup crumbs.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk and vanilla.
Add mixture to larger crumb mixture and mix. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon pie filling on top. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix flour, oleo and pecans.
Press into large baking dish. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Mix together sugar, cream cheese and whipped topping.
Spread on cooled crust.
Boil berries, sugar and water.
Cook 1 minute.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup water.
Add to blueberries and cook until thick.
Cool.
Spread on cream cheese. Top with whipped topping.

title: fluffy buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks with rotary beater. Add remaining ingredients except egg whites and beat until smooth. Gently fold in egg whites.
Pour onto hot griddle.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Combine ground beef and egg in large bowl; mix well. Add oats, onion, green pepper, 1/2 the ketchup, milk soup mix 2 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to ground beef mixture and mix well. Shape into a loaf and put in baking dish. Bake for 45 minutes. Combine remaining Worcestershire sauce and ketchup in a small bowl and mix well. Take meat loaf out of oven and spread mixture on top. Bake another 10 minutes or until cooked through.

title: grilled hot bites
directions: Slice jalapenos in half.
Clean out seeds.
Stuff with cream cheese and wrap in half a strip of bacon.
Secure with a toothpick and grill for approximately 25 minutes.

title: ciambolotto
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
in large mixing bowl and mix with electric
mixer.
Batter should be thicker than a normal cake mix batter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: french herbed chicken
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in hot fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Drain excess fat in skillet. Add remaining ingredients, except celery and bay leaf.
Heat, scraping up browned pieces.
Pour over chicken.
Tuck in celery and bay leaf.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Remove bay leaf and celery.
Serves 4.

title: no crust custard pie(easy, quick and delicious)
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sugar, nutmeg, flour, salt and milk. Beat for 2 minutes on medium.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together in large bowl all dry ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and add liquid mixture.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans or 6 (6 x 3 x 2-inch) greased foil pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for large pans and 40 minutes for small pans.
Remove from oven and cool 5 minutes before removing from pans.
Finish cooling on wire racks.

title: marinated carrots with artichokes
directions: Cut carrots into 1/2-inch thick slanting slices.
Heat olive oil in large pan; add carrots.
Cover and cook until partially tender (about 8 minutes).
Add water, lemon juice and peel, salt, sugar and pepper.

Bring to boiling; add artichoke hearts and cook until just tender or if using canned artichokes, warm through. Lift out vegetables with a slotted spoon and arrange in bowl. Cool vegetables and cooking liquid separately, then pour cooled liquid over vegetables and refrigerate several hours.

title: hospitality punch(makes 8 five ounce drinks)
directions: Mix in punch bowl. Add cake of ice. Decorate with orange and lemon slices.

title: grandma squire's church window cookies
directions: Cook margarine and chips until melted and smooth.
Let cool. Add nuts and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Form into rolls on 2 or 3 sheets of wax paper covered with coconut.
Chill, slice and serve.

title: purple lady
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in boiling water.
Add blueberries and pineapple; mix well.
Chill until gelatin mixture is partially set.

title: vegetable puffs
directions: Beat the eggs and milk together.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and pepper into eggs and milk.
Beat until well mixed.
Add mashed potatoes and beat again.
Stir the well drained corn kernels in with spoon or rubber spatula along with chopped parsley.
Drop by spoonful onto shortening which has been heated until an inch square of bread will brown in a minute (1 1/2-inches of shortening in pan).
Each puff must be turned in a few minutes, so fry only 4 or 5 at a time.

title: bully's east cream of chicken soup(serves about 10)
directions: Bring to boil the chicken in the water and chicken base. Simmer until cooked.
Remove chicken; reserve the stock.
Discard skin and bones and set aside the chicken meat, sliced into bite-size pieces.

title: 12 layer ribbon jello
directions: Take cherry jello
and	dissolve
with	1
cup	boiling water. Separate into 2
different
bowls	1/2
cup
each.
To first, add 1/2 cup sour cream and whip.
Pour on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and let set
up in refrigerator.
To the remaining 1/2 cup of jello, add 3
teaspoons of cold water.
Pour on top of set up jello.
Allow this	to set up.
Repeat this with all kinds of jello in
colors
as follows:
cherry, orange, lemon, lime, lemon and blue food
coloring,
added
to
make
a
blue color, then black raspberry.
Top
with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chocolate or multi-colored sprinkles.

title: oyster stew
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, strain 1 cup oyster liquor.
Add oysters, butter and pepper.
Over low heat, cook until oysters curl around the edges.
In a small saucepan, over medium heat, heat half and half and milk until tiny bubbles form around edges of saucepan. Add to oyster mixture.
Ladle soup into bowls. Garnish with oyster crackers.

title: creamed chicken and fettuccine
directions: Cut each chicken breast in half. Beat egg lightly in a small bowl. Combine flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper on wax paper. Dip chicken in egg. Dredge in flour mixture. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook 10 minutes or until tender. Remove to a platter. Keep warm. Add 2 tablespoons butter to drippings in skillet. Add mushrooms and cook over medium heat until tender. Stir in 2 tablespoons flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute. Stir in milk and sherry. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Stir in cheese until melted.
Remove 1 cup sauce. Add pasta to sauce in skillet, tossing to coat. Arrange on platter with chicken. Pour remaining 1 cup sauce over chicken. Sprinkle pasta with parsley.

title: black bean (pickled) pork
directions: Heat pot.
Add garlic and ginger.
Brown pork and spareribs. Wash black beans slightly and then mash fine.
Combine with the remaining ingredients and pour over spareribs; mix thoroughly. Simmer for 1 hour until tender.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese and sugar at low speed until soft and fluffy.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add to peanut butter mixture and mix well.
Add milk and beat.
Remove beaters and fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into graham pie crust.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine and press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: hamburger and spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bell pepper; drain and set aside. Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Melt butter; add Worcestershire sauce, tomato puree, soup, salt, pepper and 6 ounces cheese.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour into baking dish and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 375° until cheese on top melts.

title: breakfast puffs
directions: Mix shortening, 1/2 cup of sugar and egg.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg together.
Stir into shortening mixture with milk.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Immediately remove from pans, roll in butter, then in 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: mama's chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut up.
Place in bottom of casserole dish. Put in dressing and butter.
Heat soup and broth.
Pour over chicken and dressing.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.
Watch close or it will dry out.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper; drain.
Put into casserole dish.
Lay vegetables, then soup, Cheddar cheese and Tater Tots. Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.
(You may change meat to chicken, the soup to cream of chicken or cream of celery.)

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Use
fresh
or frozen blackberries.
Roll out dough and cut into 4 or 6-inch squares.
Grease bottom of baking dish or favorite
pan
with butter or margarine.
Have handy sugar and butter.
Put
a
handful of berries on dough (I hold the dough squares in palm of hand).
Now sprinkle sugar over berries and a piece of butter.
Now fold over dough square securely until each corner is sealed.
Place in corner of pan or dish.

title: crackling bread
directions: Mix corn meal, salt and soda.
Add buttermilk and cracklings. Pour into skillet and bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: chili con queso
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and most of grease.
Chop and saute peppers, onions and garlic.
Break up cheese and add to mixture in skillet making sure heat is very low.
Add bacon and chilies, chopped and drained, and drained tomatoes.
Cook over low heat 30 minutes.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.
Freezes well.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine the hamburger meat and oats or cracker crumbs.
Add just enough milk to soak them.
Add egg and mix.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Form into walnut size balls; brown in bacon grease until brown on both sides.
Pour off some of the grease.
Add the tomato sauce and enough water to cover.
Place cover on skillet; cook on low heat for about 45 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Bring water to boil, potatoes, onion and bouillon included with water.
Boil for 20 minutes if using cubed potatoes, 10 minutes if using hash browns.
Add vegetables and boil 10 minutes, or until done.
Add soup and cheese and heat through.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix above ingredients and pour into 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: fudgy crumbs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Microwave chocolate and margarine in large microwavable bowl on High 2 minutes or until margarine is melted. Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate until well blended.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and walnuts until well blended.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out with fudgy crumbs.
Do not overbake. Cool in pan and cut into squares.

title: dang good pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
This will make 2 deep dish pies or 3 regular pies.
Real good.

title: chicken pie
directions: Remove
chicken
from
bone, replace chicken into broth. Place chicken in 9 x 11-inch pan; add 2 tablespoons butter and 2 tablespoons
chicken
instant bouillon.
Add enough broth to cover chicken.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, salt, eggs and vanilla together. Add zucchini. Add rest of ingredients in order listed. Mix well. Will look lumpy. Grease well either 2 large or 3 small bread tins. Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: blueberry or blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix berries, sugar, flour, salt and lemon juice. Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Dot with butter. Place in preheated oven for about 15 minutes or until mixture is hot and bubbling. Have pie crust at room temperature and cut into strips for cobbler pie. Place strips on berries and cook until brown, approximately 15 minutes.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven. Turn heat to 325°.
Bake 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes before turning out.

title: spicy herb marinade
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
In shallow dish or plastic bag, pour over chicken, beef or pork.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Remove meat from marinade; heat marinade.
Grill or broil as desired, basting frequently with marinade.
Refrigerate leftover meat. Makes about 3/4 cup.

title: kids' finger jello
directions: Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Let set and cut into desired shapes.

title: broccoli and rice with cheese
directions: Mix broccoli and rice while hot.
Add margarine, Cheez Whiz and soup.
Mix well and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Fry onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Add cut up chicken and cook until brown.
Put chicken, onion and butter mix into a large bowl and, with a mixer, beat in cream cheese until it looks like tuna spread.
Add Cheddar cheese. Mix well.
Spread rolls out.
Place a heaping tablespoonful of chicken mix on roll.
Roll into crescent shape.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal butter crisps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix brown sugar, butter and egg thoroughly.
Stir in oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Shape dough by tablespoonfuls into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet; press down with fork.
Bake until almost no indentation remains when touched, about 9 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from baking sheet.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut stems from mushrooms, finely chop enough stems to measure 1/3 cup.
Cook and stir chopped mushroom stem and onion in 3 tablespoons butter until tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon butter in shallow baking dish until melted.
Fill mushroom caps with stuffing.
Place mushroom caps filled side up in baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes.
Set oven control to broil or 550°.
Broil 3 to 4-inches from heat 2 minutes. Serve hot.

title: tortilla pizza(lighter eating - 9 points)
directions: Preheat oven to 350-375°. Place tortilla on baking sheet, spread sauce over tortillas, then add half of the cheese, pepperoni and lots of veggies and then add the rest of cheese on top. Bake until cheese is melted and tortillas are golden.

title: magic quiche
directions: Heat oven
to
Grease
or 10-inch quiche pan. Spread bacon,
cheese, onion and corn in pan.
Blend remaining ingredients for
1	minute.
Pour
over bacon mixture and bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces seasoned with salt and pepper. Put in large pot add water.
Cook on medium heat until chicken is tender, (about one hour).

title: chicken oscar(serves 4 people)
directions: Pound chicken breasts to flatten. Bread chicken breasts and set aside. Saute chicken breasts in oil. Heat Krab meat in a little butter; same with asparagus. Make Hollandaise Sauce.

title: deep dish ham pie
directions: Blend margarine, flour, salt and pepper in saucepan.
Stir in milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add onion, ham, eggs and peas.
Pour into 10 x 10-inch baking dish.
Pat biscuit dough to fit the baking dish.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until top is light brown.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: beef-o-lay(a taco flavored dinner dish)
directions: Brown meat.
Add tomato paste, water and onion.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
For each serving, put meat mixture on plate.
Top with lettuce, cheese, tomatoes and corn chips.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine sour cream and marshmallows in a large bowl.
Stir until marshmallows are well coated.
Add all other ingredients and stir until well coated.
Add all other ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Refrigerate.

title: mountainside feast
directions: Fry, boil or bake fish until done.
Bless it.
Warm loaves in oven; separate into pieces.
Bless it as well.
Invite 5,000 of your closest friends and/or relatives.
Jesus is the host.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Boil whole, unpeeled sweet potatoes until tender.
Drain, peel and cut into thick slices.
Drain peaches, save the juice.
Stir the brown sugar into the juice until dissolved.
Put a layer of potatoes in a baking pan.
Spread half of the peach slices over the potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with the ginger.
Repeat this step for second layer.
Pour brown sugar mixture over potatoes.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: johnny mazette
directions: Saute peppers, celery, onions and meat in butter.
Add salt. Reduce heat and cook 10 minutes.
Stir in sauce from soups.
Cook 5 minutes.
Cook noodles (1 pound) according to package directions. Drain.
Pour noodles into 14 x 10 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Stir gently until well mixed.
Sprinkle 2 cups grated American cheese on top or use sliced cheese to cover top.
Bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Mix in milk and shortening; stir in nuts.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Wash mushrooms gently in cool water or wipe with a damp cloth. Remove stems, and chop.
Saute onion in butter.
Add chopped stems, pecans, bread crumbs, lemon juice and salt; mix well.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler.
Blend sugar, cornstarch and salt into a saucepan and slowly stir in milk.
Cook until mixture thickens and becomes bubbly.
Blend in chocolate.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and margarine.
Stir until margarine melts.
Chill.
Makes 1 cup.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and flour.
In a small bowl, mix vinegar, ketchup, brown sugar and cornstarch.
In a large skillet, heat the oil over medium-high heat.
Cook chicken until golden brown.
Remove from pan and cover with foil when done.
Increase heat to high.
At this point, add a little oil, if necessary, and cook vegetables until crisp-tender, approximately 1 minute.
Add the vinegar mixture and bring to a boil, stirring until thickened.
Stir in pineapple.
Serve spooned over the top of warmed chicken breasts.

title: scalloped pork chops
directions: Place browned pork chops on top of potatoes. Put butter over potatoes. Mix onion soups and flour together with 1 1/2 cans of water. Pour soup mixture over chops and potatoes. Salt and pepper to taste. Cover with foil. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until potatoes are soft, at 350°.

title: garlic cod(with celery and onions)
directions: Mix flour, garlic and salt together. Coat cod in flour mixture. In skillet, add oil and butter. Place coated cod in skillet on medium. Sprinkle parsley flakes on cod and cook 5 minutes until lightly browned. Turn and add more parsley flakes. Cut onions in large 1 inch pieces. Cut celery on a slant 1 1/2 inches. Add to skillet. Cover and cook on low 10 minutes, or until celery is slightly tender. Serves 4 to 6.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook stew beef in water to cover, until tender.
Add vegetables to meat and cook until vegetables are tender.
