In a skillet, put oil and diced onions; fry until brown.
Stir onion mixture into pot of meat and vegetables.
Simmer 3 minutes or until stew has thickened.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar; let stand 1 hour or so.
Bring rhubarb and sugar to hard boil; boil for 5 minutes.
Remove; add strawberry jello.
Stir well.
Pour into hot jars; seal as you do with other jams.

title: mom's custard rhubarb pie
directions: Place rhubarb into unbaked pie shell.
Mix eggs, sugar, flour and milk together and pour over fruit.
(Mix flour and sugar together to help prevent lumps and then add to eggs.)
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.

title: fast meal
directions: Place in whatever size pan for the amount of broccoli and chicken you have.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator dill pickles
directions: Boil vinegar, salt and water for 5 minutes.
Divide other ingredients (spices) equally into 3 (1-quart) pickle jars.
Pack cucumbers loosely into jars.
Spoon hot liquid slowly into jars. Cover with enameled metal lids and allow to cool.
Refrigerate for 2 plus weeks before eating.
(These pickles stay crisp better than canned pickles because jars are not boiled.)

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Fold in peach pie filling, well drained can of fruit cocktail and marshmallows.
Pour into bowl and top with coconut.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Sprinkle sugar and flour over sliced rhubarb.
Place in 5 x 9-inch pan or large pie plate.
Mix the remaining ingredients and spread over rhubarb mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until rhubarb is done.

title: ranch house beans
directions: Combine bacon, onion and hamburger.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in large oven casserole dish. Serves several.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients together.
Add all dry ingredients. Mix well and fold in apples.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Pears may be substituted for apples.

title: stir-fried cabbage
directions: Halve the cabbage; thinly slice crosswise and rinse with cold water.
In a large pot, cook the bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; drain on paper towel and crumble.
Return 3 tablespoons of bacon drippings to pot.
Add cabbage, onion, caraway seed and rosemary to pot, stirring occasionally, until cabbage is tender (if needed, add 2 tablespoons water), about 15 minutes.
Stir in crumbled bacon, salt and pepper.

title: gelatin poke cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and oil and beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan and bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.
Dissolve jell-o as directed on package.
Poke holes in cool cake and pour jell-o over the cake.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Frost with Dream Whip or Cool Whip.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9-inch loaf pan. Mix all ingredients; beat 30 seconds.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, about 65 to 70 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Set aside bread crumbs, cheese and butter.
Mix all remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Pour in casserole dish.
Mix together bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle butter on top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 45 minutes.

title: bachelor button cookies
directions: Cream margarine. Add sugar and cream well. Beat egg and add to sugar mixture.
Add coconut, chopped walnuts and cherries.
Blend well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture slowly.
If mixture seems too thick, add a few drops of milk. Drop from teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mom's corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Crumble soda crackers on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cover raisins with water and cook 5 minutes; drain.
Combine sugar and flour; add to raisins along with sour cream, egg yolks and margarine. Cook very slowly, stirring until mixture thickens. Add vanilla and pour into baked pie shell.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Place chicken in flat dish.
Pour buttermilk over.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Mix flour, salt and pepper in a paper bag.
Drain chicken.
Toss, one at a time, in flour mixture. Place on waxed paper for 10 minutes to dry.

title: transit pizza
directions: Step 1:
Pick up phone; dial Pizza Hut.

title: coating for oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with foil.
Heat margarine in pan in oven until melted.
Mix baking mix, paprika, salt and pepper; coat chicken.
Place, skin side down, in pan. Bake uncovered 35 minutes.
Turn.
Bake until done, about 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hot sausage dip
directions: Brown and drain sausage in a large pot.
Add remaining ingredients except for wine.
Simmer, stirring often, until cheese is melted and mixture thickens.
Add wine.
Serve with corn chips.

title: fresh green beans
directions: Clean beans.
Boil in salted water about 10 to 15 minutes. Do not overcook.
Drain.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown hamburger and bell pepper.
Drain and set aside.
Peel and slice potatoes lengthwise.
Slice onions into rings.
In a large, deep baking dish, alternate thin layers of potatoes, onions, hamburger, mushroom soup and salt and pepper (about 3 layers of each).
Top with a thin layer of potatoes, sprinkled with Cheddar cheese.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are soft.

title: pink gelatin salad
directions: Heat pineapple and jello to boiling point.
Set aside to cool. Add cottage cheese and whipped topping.
Pour into bowl or mold and refrigerate.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Combine all ingredients and put in crock pot. Cover with towel. Cook on low 8 hrs.

title: sweet and sour wieners
directions: Melt grape jelly over medium heat.
Stir in chili sauce and heat through.
Add meat and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve warm.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine all 5 ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: horchata(mexican rice drink)
directions: Mix together rice, water, cinnamon stick & sugar.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cool mixture, discard cinnamon stick.
Puree in a blender.
Use a spoon to push mixture through a medium mesh sieve.
If it seems stiff, add enough cold water to bring it to the consistency of cream.
Add lime if desires and sugar to taste.
Chill & serve over ice.
Makes two generous glasses.

title: apricot buns
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar, add the well beaten eggs. Add flour, salt and baking powder sifted together alternately with milk.
Turn out onto a floured board, divide into 12 or 14 portions.
Work each smoothly, then roll out about 1/2-inch thick. Divide the fruit among the portions of dough.
Gather the dough up over the apricots, pinching edges well together.
Brush over with milk.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Lay on greased pan and bake 30 minutes in moderate oven (350° to 375°).

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter and pour into large pan.
Fold in the box of Crispix, gently.
Mix thoroughly. Put powdered sugar and cocoa in a paper bag.
Pour Crispix mixture into the bag and shake to coat thoroughly.
Pour onto waxed paper and let cool and dry.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Serve dip with crackers.

title: german potato salad
directions: Put bacon and green onions in 1-quart casserole dish and cover. Microwave at High (100%) until bacon is light brown, 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir in vinegar, sugar and salt.
Set aside.

title: cream cheese pudding dessert
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter.
Mix well; press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 15 minutes. Combine cream cheese, sugar and milk in medium bowl.
With electric mixer at medium speed, beat until smooth.
Fold in 1/2 whipped cream.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding and milk as directed.
Pour over cream cheese.
Chill several hours before serving.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on pudding.

title: orange sherbet jello salad
directions: Stir Jell-O into boiling water. Pour into large container and add sherbet. Mix until melted. Add pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and nuts. Stir, then stir in Cool Whip until no lumps show. Chill 6 hours or overnight.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; heat margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When margarine is melted, pour batter on top of melted margarine.
Top with any fruit of your choice, canned or fresh.
Top with sugar.
Cook 25 minutes at 425°.

title: fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (175°C).
Butter a 7 x 4 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Sift together the flour, the salt, cinnamon and baking powder.
Using the whisks of the mixer at high speed, beat eggs until frothy.
Pour into a mixing bowl.
Cut the softened butter into pieces and again using the whisks, cream with sugar. Gradually pour in the beaten egg and beat well.
Replace the whisks with the plastic blade; add the flour to the mixture and process at low speed until just blended.
Transfer to a bowl.
Mix in all the dried fruits, the candied cherries and the vanilla.
Pour into the greased pan.
Level mixture by shaking the pan.
Bake in a preheated oven for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: fanny farmers fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil, stirring constantly.
Keep at a hard rolling boil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add margarine.
Let melt and beat by hand for 2 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla.
Beat 10 to 15 minutes with mixer.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: zucchini supreme
directions: Cook zucchini in a small amount of boiling, salted water until tender crisp; drain.
Place in greased 1-1/2 quart casserole.
Melt butter in same pan as used for zucchini.
Stir in sour cream, cheese, salt and paprika.
Cook over low heat stirring constantly until cheese is melted (do not overheat or boil). Remove from heat; stir in egg yolk and chives.
Toss bread crumbs with melted butter.
Stir cheese mixture into zucchini and cover with bread crumb mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until slightly brown on top.

title: mustard and anchovy dunk
directions: Combine mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add mustard, garlic, tarragon, parsley and anchovies.
Mix well.
Add pepper to taste. Use as dip for fresh veggies such as cherry tomatoes, carrots, cucumbers, zucchini, peppers, etc.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: "lite" dilled round steak(serves 4)
directions: Trim fat from meat.
Cut meat into 4 serving size pieces. Spray a cold large skillet with spray coating or add a little oil. Add meat and brown on medium heat.
While meat is browning, thinly slice onion.
Carefully add water, onion, lemon juice, bouillon, garlic salt, dill weed and pepper to skillet.
Bring to boiling, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour until meat is tender.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Mix in drink mix and pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Pour over ice. Garnish with orange rings and cherries.

title: christmas nut roll
directions: Make crumbs of Ritz crackers.
Place in dishpan or large bowl. Cut up dates
into	crumbs	first,	then
add
all	other ingredients except milk and butter.
Set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add condensed milk to crumb mixture.
Mix well.	Add melted butter and mix well.
(I
use my hands at this point for mixing.) Work mixture
adding
enough
evaporated
milk to make good consistency.
Shape into rolls the size of a stack pack of Ritz crackers and roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Store in
refrigerator.
Cut
with
sharp	knife
when serving.
Will keep up
to one month in refrigerator if wrapped well.
Yield: 6 to 7 rolls.
Each roll serves 16 to 18 people.

title: shannon's 24 hour salad
directions: In a large covered salad bowl, layer all ingredients in their listed order.
Cover lightly. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Will keep several days.

title: turtle cake with icing
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour half of the batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops from green peppers.
Discard seeds and membranes. Chop enough of the tops to make 1/4 cup and set aside.
Cook the whole green peppers, uncovered, in boiling water for 5 minutes. Invert to drain well.

title: pepper relish
directions: I make a small bag with spices to boil in mixture.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Beat together and bring to a boil.
Add 1 cup (or more if desired) of long grain cooked rice and 2 tablespoons butter.
Heat about 5 minutes.
Do not boil.
If thicker soup is desired, cut down on milk.

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 8-inch square baking pan.
In medium bowl, combine baking mix and cocoa.
Stir in 1 cup condensed milk, 1/4 cup syrup and vanilla until blended.
Spoon evenly in prepared pan.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into glass serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 each of the wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat layering 2 to 3 times, ending with pudding.
Cover and chill.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 10 to 14 servings.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil together the first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Add the soda and vanilla.
Put in large pan.
Pour liquid over popcorn. Bake it for 1 hour at 250°; stir every 15 minutes.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Scrub and cut up potatoes (amount needed for your family). Put a small amount of water in a casserole dish.
Pour melted butter over potatoes in casserole dish.
Use 1/4 cup butter for 4 to 6 people.
Add salt and pepper and parsley, if desired.
Bake about 1 hour.
Stir to coat potatoes.
This recipe can also be microwaved.

title: chris' chili mix-up
directions: Heat chili until hot.
Remove from heat.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Put in a bowl and cover with Cheddar cheese.
Eat up!

title: roast beef
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
If roast is untied, tie at 3 inch intervals with cotton twine.
Place roast in pan and season with salt, garlic powder, and pepper.
Add more or less seasonings to taste.

Roast in oven for 60 minutes (20 minutes per pound). Remove from oven, cover loosely with foil, and let rest for 15-20 minutes. Slice thinly and serve with gravy, mashed potatoes, salad and veggie of your choice.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Saute in small amount of oil the celery and onion.
Remove from heat and add hamburger.
Brown and add salt.
Add cream of chicken soup, mushroom soup, water, soy sauce and rice.
Mix together. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with Chinese noodles or potato chips.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: jt's tex-mex chili
directions: Heat chili stir constantly to a boil.
Pour into a serving dishes.
Feeds two hungry Texans or only one if really hungry. Add a generous amount of catsup or Ketchapeno and some of your favorite grated cheese.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon; remove bones and flake. Make bread into fine crumbs in food processor. Combine all ingredients except oil. (Add a little milk if mixture seems too dry.) Form 10 to 11 patties. Pan-fry in lightly oiled skillet about 5 minutes or until lightly browned; turn halfway through cooking time. Drain on absorbent paper towels.

title: company chicken
directions: Skin chicken breasts, season to taste with salt and pepper. Add water, cover and cook until almost done.
Soften cream cheese in a separate dish.
Add sour cream and soups.
Mix together well. Add broth from cooked chicken.
Wrap chicken with thin smoked beef slices.
Pour cream mixture over chicken and beef and cook until done.
Serve over rice or creamed potatoes.

title: pumpkin raisin muffins
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs with wooden spoon in large bowl.
Add pumpkin mix; stir well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients.
Line muffin cups.
Pour mixture into cups, filling 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400° or until firm.
Makes 12 to 18 muffins.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Shake sauce ingredients together in jar.
Pour over fried hamburger (still in skillet.)
Rinse jar out with 1/2 cup water and pour this over hamburger.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Bake pork chops for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
(Mix rice, chicken soup and margarine in bowl; set aside.)
After chops bake for 30 minutes, take out of oven and spread rice mixture over chops.
Bake for 30 minutes more.

title: english toffee
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Stir in sugar.
Constantly stir for 5 minutes.
Add walnuts and cook 5 minutes more, stirring constantly.
Turn to high heat and cook, stirring constantly, about 2 minutes or until it turns medium brown.
Spread on ungreased cookie sheet.
Pour chocolate chips over and spread when melted. Refrigerate until cool.
Break into pieces.

title: seafood and avocado salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together well.
Serve with Thousand Island dressing.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out on lightly floured area about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° until lightly brown.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into container with a lid.
Shake well. Ready to serve.

title: gone all afternoon stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together; no need to brown the meat.
Cook in Dutch oven for 5 hours at 300° or in crock-pot all day.
Resist the urge to lift the cover for a peek.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: rolls
directions: Combine yeast and egg; set aside.
Combine the last 4 ingredients in a bowl and stir until blended.
Cool until lukewarm, then add enough flour, about 1 1/2 cups, and beat until smooth.
Add enough flour and knead on floured bread board until not sticky.
Place in greased bowl in warm place until dough rises to double.
Shape in rolls as desired and bake in 400° oven until when touched with finger, the rolls spring back into shape.
Makes a dozen cloverleaf rolls.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain juice from clams and pour over vegetables in a saucepan. Add enough water to barely cover and simmer, covered, over medium heat until barely tender.
In meantime, melt butter, add flour and blend.
Cook, stirring constantly.
Add cream and stir with wire whip until smooth and thick (important).
Add undrained vegetables and clams; heat through.
Season with salt, pepper and sugar to taste.

title: coke salad(serves 24)
directions: Drain juice from fruits adding enough water to make 2 cups. Heat this to dissolve jello.
Mash cheese into warm jello (do not whip).
Cut up cherries and arrange with fruit in large flat casserole or cake pan.
Pour jello mixture over fruit and pour Coke over this, mixing slightly.
Arrange pecan halves on top.

title: low-fat chewy spice cookies
directions: Combine brown sugar, applesauce, molasses and egg whites until well blended. Combine flour, baking soda and spices in separate bowl;

stir into molasses mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto baking sheets that have been lightly coated with nonstick cooking spray. Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 375° for 8-10 minutes. Yields about 3 dozen cookies.

title: sausage stir-fry
directions: Chop broccoli flowerets and part of stalk.
Saute in skillet with some oil and some soy sauce for flavoring.
Add sliced sausage and onion.
Saute until tender, not mushy.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk and salt.
Cook and stir until mixture boils.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add sugar. Stir.
Pour into greased baking dish and set aside.
To beaten eggs add 2 cups of milk and evaporated milk, raisins and stir.
Stir into rice mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Put into a 300° preheated oven.
Place over a pan of hot water.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: delicate jam cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt and all spices together.
Work in sugar gradually until mixture is creamy.
Add beaten eggs all at once and beat hard.
Stir in jam.
Mix flour mixture alternately with milk and stir only until flour disappears.
Don't beat.
Pour into 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut thin slice from stem end of each pepper.
Remove all seeds and membranes.
Wash pepper thoroughly, inside and out.
Heat 1 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt to boiling.
Add peppers; cook 5 minutes and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Lightly stuff each pepper with 1/3 of the meat mixture.
Stand peppers upright in ungreased baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Yields 4.

title: crabmeat casserole or dip
directions: In saucepan, saute celery and shallots in 1 stick of butter until soft.
Add cream cheese and seasonings and blend.
Remove from heat and add crabmeat, mixing lightly.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars until smooth.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together and add to creamed mixture.
Then add corn flakes, oatmeal, pecans and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until light brown (optional).
Place cherry half or 2 to 3 chocolate chips in center of each cookie before baking.

title: pimiento cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: caesar of the sea
directions: In blender container, combine oil, lemon juice, egg, garlic clove, salt, pepper and sugar.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Stir in anchovy fillet.
In large salad bowl, combine romaine, tuna, Parmesan and dressing.
Toss to coat greens.
Add croutons and toss again lightly.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, celery and green pepper.
Add water and let simmer 1 hour.
Add chow mein, beef broth, Chinese vegetables and mushrooms; simmer 2 hours approximately.
Season with soy sauce and thicken with cornstarch.
Serve with rice.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Add 3 cups water to Jell-O and tapioca.
Let boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add drained pineapple and oranges.
Add Cool Whip and refrigerate until set.

title: dream whip dessert
directions: Beat together 1 large package cream cheese and 1 cup sugar. Prepare two envelopes Dream Whip.
Fold Dream Whip into mixture. Pour into crushed graham cracker crust or pie shell.
Top with blueberry or cherry pie filling and more Dream Whip.

title: curry dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium mixing bowl; mix well. Serve dip with raw vegetables.

title: sugar-free banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: taco casserole
directions: Mix soups, chilies and enchilada sauce; do not cook.
Crumble tortilla chips and place in bottom of baking dish.
Pour on meat mixture, then pour on soup mixture.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Cheese will melt and start to bubble when done.

title: angel biscuits(makes 48 half inch biscuits)
directions: Preheat
oven to 450°.	Butter a baking dish or line it with parchment paper and set aside.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar for 20 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time. Gradually add the flour and beat well.
Then add lemon extract and 7-Up.
Pour into well-oiled Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool 8 to 10 minutes and then dust with powdered sugar or glaze.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes.
Drain.
Saute onion and garlic in margarine. Add milk and boiled potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients except apples with an electric mixer, then stir in apples and turn into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: wine jelly
directions: You will also need paraffin and 4 half pint jelly glasses.

title: cinnamon coffee
directions: Combine dry milk powder, coffee, sugar and cinnamon.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 1 cup of mix.

title: pecan snowballs
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add pecans and flour.
Shape into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
While hot, roll in confectioners sugar and when cool roll again.

title: roasted garlic
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove the outer layer of skin from heads of garlic.
Cut 1/2-inch off from each head straight across top and put in shallow baking pan.
Drizzle 2 teaspoons olive oil over each head and let it run between the cloves.
Cover with foil and bake 30 to 45 minutes until garlic is tender.
To serve, peel off cloves and squeeze the roasted garlic onto toasted bread or veggies.

title: english strawberry trifle
directions: Prepare
cake
as
directed
on
box.
Pour batter into oblong pan and bake as directed on package.
Remove from oven, and with toothpick or fork, stick holes through the surface of the cake.

title: chocolate chip cookies with a twist
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place length of foil on flat surface. In a large bowl, beat oils, brown sugar, milk and vanilla on medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg; beat well.
Stir together flour, salt and baking soda.
Gradually add to sugar mixture, beating on low speed just until blended.
Stir in wheat germ, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 3-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool 2 minutes; remove from cookie sheets to foil.

title: vanilla fudge
directions: Line an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan with foil, extending foil over edges of pan.	Butter foil; set aside.
Butter sides of a heavy 2-quart saucepan.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli	according
to package directions; drain well. Cook rice.	Combine cream cheese and remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread; cut into 1-inch cubes.
Place bread cubes in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cream cheese cubes.
Combine eggs, milk and syrup in a large bowl, stirring with a wire whisk until blended.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until set and golden.
Serve immediately.

title: flossy's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line jelly roll pan with whole graham crackers.
Boil butter, margarine and sugar for 2 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool, then break into pieces.

title: classic white cake
directions: Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and eggs.
Add together the flour, baking soda, salt and sour cream and mix.
Bake in greased Bundt pan 60 to 90 minutes at 350°.

title: mary's peanut butter fudge
directions: Put milk, sugar, syrup and salt in 3-quart saucepan.
Over medium to high heat, bring to a boil.
Once ingredients begin to boil, be sure to stir as much as possible.
After about 15 to 20 minutes, begin checking a small amount of mixture in cup of cold water.
When mixture forms a soft ball in cold water, remove pan from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until mixture is smooth.
Put into greased
pan or dish.
Put in refrigerator until hard.
Cut and serve.

title: beef-stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in half lengthwise. Scoop out pulp. Place cut side up in baking dish. Chop eggplant.
In pan, saut chopped eggplant, onion and garlic in oil for 5 minutes until eggplant is soft.
Remove from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.

Spoon meat and rice mix into eggplant shells. Cover with foil. Pierce foil in several places to allow steam to escape. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes until fork-tender. Remove foil. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered about 4 minutes longer or until cheese is melted. Cut each in half to serve.

title: great grandma bennett's pork and sauerkraut casserole
directions: In a large skillet, saute carrots, celery, onions and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Set aside.
Add sausage, sauerkraut and apples to skillet mixture and mix well.
Combine sour cream, parsley, salt and pepper with rest.
Pour into a deep baking dish.
Cover with
8 cups mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until the potatoes are browned.

title: jello poke cake
directions: Place cake layers, top sides up, in 2 clean 8 or 9-inch layer pans.
Prick each cake with large, 2-pronged fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Dissolve Jell-O and pour over cake layers.
Chill for at least 4 hours.
Dip in warm water for about 10 seconds to unmold layers.
Turn onto serving plate one layer at a time. Frost.
Repeat with second layer.
Place on top of first layer and frost.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil fryer or hen.
Add salt and pepper in water.
Save broth. Debone.
Saute seasonings in butter.
Add mushroom soup and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add chicken and about 1 cup broth. Boil noodles in chicken broth until tender.
Drain and layer noodles and mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients, then add carrots and nuts; mix by hand.
Pour into Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak crumbs in 3/4 cup milk for 10 minutes.
Fry onion in 2 tablespoons fat until brown; add meat, salt, onion and egg to bread mixture.
Form into balls and fry in remaining 2 tablespoons of fat until brown.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons flour over all, add 1/2 cup milk and cover and cook 10 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Sprinkle sliced peaches with lemon juice and sugar.
Let stand one hour.
Drain.
Measure one cup of syrup.
Add to cornstarch; blend.
Stir over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo, salt and extract.
Cool.
Place peaches in shell.

title: raisin bread pudding
directions: Mix last three ingredients.
Pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables and mix together.
Combine sugar, vinegar, peanut oil, salt and black pepper; bring this mixture to boil. Pour over vegetables and put in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine beaten egg yolks, sugar, lemon juice, lemon peel and salt; cook in a double boiler, stirring constantly until mixture coats a spoon.
Cool; fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour filling into crust.
Place in freezer and freeze firm.
Serve frozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into unbaked 9-inch pastry pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Brown pork chops thoroughly on both sides and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Place one slice of onion on each pork chop, then spoon soup mixture over onion.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon drops
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; set aside.
Beat margarine, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Beat in juice and peel. Stir in flour mixture until smooth.
Refrigerate covered 1 to 2 hours.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on lightly greased sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: devil dog sandwiches
directions: Place bacon between layers of paper towels and microwave 3 1/2 to 4 minutes (it will not be crispy).
Split hot dogs lengthwise, not cutting through.
Mix together ham, cheese, olives and mustard.
Spread on inside of hot dog and press together.
Wrap slice of bacon around each hot dog and place in bowl.
Wrap sandwich loosely in a paper towel.
Do 3 sandwiches in microwave at a time for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.

title: decorating frosting
directions: Mix shortening and flavorings until fluffy.
Stir in powdered sugar, one cup at a time (this will be very stiff).
Mix in milk or water.
Beat until fluffy.
Frosting may be tinted to any color.
This is a very good frosting for decorating cakes or cookies.
Store in refrigerator up to two weeks.
Frosting may be doubled if you use a heavy duty mixer.

title: jambalya
directions: Saute green onions, onion and celery until tender, set aside. Boil chicken and sausage until chicken is tender done.
Remove chicken and sausage and cook rice in the broth where they were cooked.
After the rice has been cooked stir in chicken, sausage, sauteed vegetables, parsley and Kitchen Bouquet until it is a light caramel color.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Pop corn in oil.
Melt margarine and marshmallows.
Stir in peanuts, popcorn and M&M's.
Pour mixture into greased Bundt pan. Press down well.
Cool before slicing.
Delicious and colorful. Great for parties.
At Christmas use red and green M&M's.
At Easter, use pastel M&M's.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop beef finely.
Save one package for topping.
In large bowl, mix together well.
Roll into ball.
Cover ball with remaining package of chopped beef.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: corn butter
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup water for several minutes.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over gelatin and whiz until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and liquify until smooth as cream.
Pour into a bowl and cover and refrigerate.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and add pineapple and eggs; mix.
Place in pan and sprinkle over top brown sugar and nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday appetizer pie
directions: Blend cheese and milk.
Add beef and onion; mix well.
Stir in sour cream; fill an 8-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: tuna potato casserole
directions: Mix together the soup, milk, tuna and 3/4 cup grated cheese. Add potatoes and put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop or grind peppers and onions. Cover with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes. Drain and cover again with boiling water. Let stand for 10 minutes.
Drain once more.
Add all other ingredients. Mix well and seal in hot, sterilized jars.
Heat in a slow oven for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry cream cheese squares
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, water and blueberries. Cook while stirring over medium heat until sauce bubbles and thickens. Cool.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter for approximately 2 minutes. Mix all ingredients except eggs.
At this point, check for proper seasoning and adjust as needed.
Add eggs, mixing well.
Bake in oiled, heavy iron skillet for 30 to 45 minutes in 375° oven. Serves 12.
A tried, tested and much loved recipe.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together first five ingredients and spread on two dinner plates or on one large platter.
Pour the seafood sauce evenly over the cream cheese mixture.
Drain crab meat and sprinkle evenly on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: pot roast and vegetables
directions: Put roast in pan of water.
Add green beans, potatoes, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook for 3 hours or until roast is tender.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugars, eggs and oil.
Add zucchini and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into two 5 x 8-inch oiled pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Test with toothpick.
Do not peel zucchini.

title: party punch
directions: Mix well and serve over ice.

title: oven glazed chicken
directions: Place chicken into a 2-quart oblong dish.
Cover with foil. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
In a small bowl combine soup, sugar, water, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Set aside.
After 30 minutes, cover chicken with sauce and bake, uncovered, 30 minutes more or until chicken is done well.
Arrange chicken over cooked noodles or rice.
Stir sauce and spoon then serve.

title: cissy's great egg dish
directions: Place bread in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese on bread.
Crumble sausage over cheese.
Beat eggs with milk and dry mustard.
Pour over all.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pitha
directions: Wash spinach and cut off stems.
Squeeze out water.
Roll tightly and cut finely.
In a large bowl, combine spinach, eggs and Feta.
Melt margarine and brush on phyllo dough.
Layer about 4 leaves.
Spread spinach and and repeat layering for about 4 more layers.
Roll up edges lightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti with clam sauce
directions: Put butter and oil in pan with chopped onions.
Cook slowly for about 20 minutes.
Onions should be cooked until transparent, not brown.
Add the basil and oregano.
Cook 5 minutes.
Chop the parsley (no stems) until minced and add to the mixture.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Add clams and the juice in the cans and cook 5 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Cook spaghetti.
Pour mixture over noodles.
Sprinkle with cheese. Serves 4 to 6.

title: sam's fruit cake
directions: Roll out vanilla wafers with a dough roller.
Put everything in a dishpan and work up.
Then put in tube pan and press firmly. Let set in refrigerator for 36 hours before cutting.

title: "sourdough" biscuits
directions: Sift flour and sugar together. Cut in shortening. Dissolve dry yeast in warm water. Add buttermilk to yeast and water. Mix all together and refrigerate several hours. Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thick and cut. Allow to rise 1 hour. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Makes about 36 medium biscuits.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight. Add meat and 2 quarts water. Simmer 2 or 3 hours until tender. Cook other ingredients separately. Add the last hour of cooking.

title: crab and brie quesadilla
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.
In a small sauce pan, combine the apples, vinegar, sugar, shallots, jalapeno, and garlic to make the chili-apple glaze.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer until the apples are translucent and soft and the vinegar has reduced by half, about 15 minutes.
Remove from the heat and cool for at least 10 minutes. Once cool, transfer to a blender or food processor and puree until smooth, about 1 minute.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Set glaze aside.
Place the crabmeat in a bowl and season, to taste, with salt and pepper.
Add the green onions and toss gently to combine.
Cover and refrigerate.
Spread the almonds on a small baking sheet and toast until golden brown, about 15 minutes. Remove from oven and allow to cool.
Place the tortillas on a work surface.
Spread 1/4 cup of the crabmeat mixture evenly over half of each tortilla.
Place 5 to 6 slices of the Brie on top of the crabmeat.
Fold the remaining half of the tortilla over, forming a half-moon shape.
Heat 2 tablespoons of the oil in a large griddle or skillet over medium heat.
When smoking hot, carefully lay the quesadilla in the oil.
Fry on 1 side until golden brown, about 2 minutes, turn with a spatula and cook until golden brown on the second side and the cheese is melted, 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove and repeat with the remaining quesadillas, adding more oil as needed. To serve, cut each quesadilla into 4 triangles.
Spread 1/4 cup of the Chili-Apple Glaze on each plate, and top with quesadilla quarters.
Garnish with the toasted almonds and chopped chives.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a pan sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: In greased baking pan, place chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place sauerkraut over chicken.
Top with Swiss cheese. Pour dressing evenly over cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° about 1 1/2 hours or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: crawfish cornbread
directions: Mix well; bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes.
Makes one large cornbread.
Almost a meal in itself served with salad.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: In medium bowl, cut margarine into flour until crumbly.
Stir in water to make ball.
Roll 3/4 of dough into 11-inch circle and put in 9-inch pie plate and trim.
Cut reserved dough into 1-inch leaves and attach to edge of pie with 1 tablespoon egg substitute.

title: chicken with wild rice
directions: Cook wild rice according to
package directions.
Drain mushrooms.
Saute mushrooms, onion and celery in butter.
Pour mushroom
soup
and 1 can of broth into
casserole
dish.
Add rice, onions, celery, mushrooms and chicken
pieces.
Bake
at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix all but chicken, cheese and Doritos.
Layer Doritos, chicken and soup mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nighty nights
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
(This recipe is to be done right before bedtime.)
Whip egg whites and sugar until stiff.
Fold in the chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop teaspoonfuls of mixture onto foil covered cookie sheet.
Insert cookie sheet full into the preheated oven.
Immediately turn off oven and leave overnight.
Do not peek! Be sure to remove them in the morning.

title: champagne punch
directions: *Use 750 ml. wine and 1 liter soda water.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir in nuts and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until batter is moistened.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Remove to wire racks and cool completely.
Can be frozen.

title: fruit sheet cake
directions: Melt oleo and add cake mix, water and eggs; mix well.
Spread in 11 x 17-inch pan.
Spoon pie filling on top of cake batter. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
When taken from the oven, ice with Powdered Sugar Glaze.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and form into balls. Place in baking dish.
Combiner the remaining three ingredients and pour over porcupines.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Cook sugar and water 10 minutes after it starts to boil.
Put in berries and boil 10 more minutes.
Add alum and boil 5 more minutes.
Skim and put in jars and seal.
Makes 4 pints.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook onion, celery and green pepper until tender.
Mix all ingredients (except cheese) and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 400° until firm and slightly brown.
Top with cheese and cover with lid to melt cheese.

title: spicy applesauce cake
directions: Mix cream, sugar and applesauce. Sift dry ingredients together and add to first mixture with raisins and nuts.
Mix and pour into greased pan. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots tender-crisp.
Heat tomato soup until warm, then mix with carrots, vegetables and seasonings.
Refrigerate.
Keeps well.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: stuffed japanese eggplant
directions: Boil eggplant until soft.
Put on plate and cut longways.
Put 1/2 lemon over the top of the eggplant.
Mince garlic.
Add cumin, salt and pepper and mix together.
Spread garlic over the eggplant.
Use the other 1/2 lemon over the top of garlic.

title: hot potato salad
directions: About 1 hour before serving, boil potatoes in jackets for about 35 minutes. Peel and cut into 1/4-inch slices. Fry bacon until tender and saute 1/2 of the onions in bowl. Mix the flour, sugar, salt and pepper. Stir in vinegar and water and mix until smooth. Add to the bacon and simmer slightly until thickened. Pour this hot dressing over potatoes. Add remaining onion, parsley, celery seeds and radishes. Serve lightly tossed and garnish with celery leaves.

title: quick pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Fill sugar box with flour and add to mixture.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for
1 1/2 hours.

title: cupcake cones
directions: Beat together butter, sugar and baking powder in a medium bowl with mixer on high speed, about 2 minutes or until pale. Add egg yolks and vanilla and beat about 2 minutes until fluffy. Reduce mixer speed to low and beat in milk, then flour just until blended. Spoon batter into each cone, pressing batter down with the back of the spoon. Bake 25 to 30 minutes until tops are a golden brown. Ice with Marshmallow Cream Icing.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar and blueberries to coat fruit.
Combine shortening, milk and egg.
Add this to the dry mixture.
Stir until mixed thoroughly.
Spoon into muffin pans.
Bake about 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: skillet goulash
directions: Cook rotini as directed. In skillet, cook ground beef, celery and onions on medium-high for 5 to 7 minutes; drain. Add cooked rotini and all remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Put all ingredients into mixing bowl and mix well.
Bake in muffin pans at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: maggie's meat loaf roll
directions: This is one of those "everything but the kitchen sink" recipes.
In other words, the base recipe is for meat loaf with vegetables and cheese filling.
Use whatever combination of vegetables, cheeses and spices you prefer.
This recipe is adaptable to most every diet plan and delicious too!!

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt cake pan at 350°
for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool and glaze.

title: kolacky(this is a not too sweet cookie.)
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese, milk and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolk.
Sift together flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture and blend well.
Refrigerate until dough is chilled, 4 hours or overnight.
Dough will be very soft.

title: mounds bars
directions: Pat the sugar, oleo and graham crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Mix together the milk and coconut. Spread over crumbs.
Bake 18 minutes longer.
Place the Hershey bar on top while still hot (or place back in oven), then spread around and cut while warm.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mashed bananas.
Mix flour and soda together, then mix all together and add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Blend all ingredients, adding shrimp last.
Chill for 1 hour. Serve with crackers.

title: crabbies(an all-time favorite!)
directions: Let margarine and cheese soften; mix with mayo and salts. Add crabmeat (shredded).
Split English muffins and then top with mixture.
Cut each muffin into fourths.
Freeze at least 1 hour or until needed.
Broil until bubbly and crisp, approximately 10 minutes.
Don't overcook.

title: low-calorie shrimp salad
directions: Mix together cottage cheese and chopped shrimp.
Peel eggs and mash until fine.
Mix with cottage cheese and shrimp.
Add the olives and salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with paprika for color.
Arrange sliced tomato over top of shrimp mixture.
Serve with crackers and beverage.
Serves 6.

title: green beans
directions: Cook green beans in water.
Mix together onion, butter, flour, salt, pepper and sour cream to make a sauce. Pour sauce over green beans and place into greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese. Put under broiler until cheese melts. Serves 3 or 4.

title: southern baked carrots
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in a greased dish at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Wash cucumber well. Trim off thin ends of cucumber.
Using a fork, make long strips down cucumber.
Cut into thin slices and place in colander.
Sprinkle with salt and leave 30 minutes. Place in a bowl to catch the cucumber liquid.
Rinse them well and pat dry.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
In a large bowl, toss together with cucumbers.

title: gocada(coconut custard)
directions: My dentures fit just fine,

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice in water and salt until tender.
Saute onion in butter until onion is tender.
Put onion, butter, tomatoes, sugar, salt and rice in baking dish and bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: garlic shrimp
directions: Heat oil and butter in a shallow casserole.
Add the shrimp and garlic; saute over high heat about 3 minutes.
Add the lemon juice, sherry, paprika, chili pepper, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve immediately, preferably in the cooking dish.

title: *cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add vinegar and chill.
Whip until fluffy.
Chop cucumber and onion and add salt.
Let this mixture set for 30 minutes or more.
Drain off liquid.
Stir in jello mixture, plus salad dressing.
Refrigerate until firm. Serves 6.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in a double boiler or over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Let cool.
Beat cream until stiff.
Stir in fruit and marshmallows.
Stir in the cooled cooked mixture of the first 4 ingredients.
Let chill 24 hours before serving.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix and simmer 6 cups of water and 4 cups sugar to dissolve sugar.

title: brown mochi
directions: Mix together the Mochiko, baking soda, sugar, water and coconut milk.
Stir in azuki.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix altogether and pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup butter.
Pour on top of potatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cover bottom of pan with Tater Tots.
Fry hamburger and put over Tots.
Mix cheese with soup and pour over all ingredients. Add more cheese and Tater Tots.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: one egg pineapple upside-down cake
directions: You will need wax paper.

title: italian layer cake
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Mix on medium speed, Ricotta, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Pour on top of cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours, until done.
Mix pudding and milk until thick; add Cool Whip.
Beat at low speed until creamy.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: "dirt"
directions: Mix together margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Mix together pudding, Cool Whip and milk; blend with cream cheese mixture.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips in double boiler or in microwave oven on controlled heat.
Stir in peanuts and noodles.
Spoon with teaspoon onto wax paper to cool.
Makes approximately 36.

title: poor man's whipped cream
directions: In a small saucepan, combine flour and milk.
Heat over medium heat until it thickens.
Remove from stove to cool.

title: basic bisquick mix
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Store in covered container (will just fit into 3 pound coffee can) up to 6 weeks at room temperature.
For longer storage, place in freezer.

title: basic yeast bread
directions: Mix yeast, warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar and let cool.
Add shortening, salt and sugar to milk and let cool.
Add yeast and 3 cups of flour; beat well.
Turn out and work in as much flour as needed.
Knead until elastic.
Put in a greased bowl, turn to grease top.
Let rise until double.
Punch down; shape into loaves or rolls.
Let rise until almost double.

title: cherry nut cake(bake off winner)
directions: Sift flour; cream butter and sugar and add vanilla and eggs 1 at a time.
Beat well.
Add flour to which other dry ingredients have been added, alternately with milk and cherry juice.
Chop the cherries and nuts and add to batter.
Bake in layers at 350°.
Ice with powdered sugar icing.

title: split pea soup
directions: In large kettle, heat peas and water to boiling.
Boil gently for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until peas are soft and mushy.
Remove bone; trim meat from bone and add to soup.
If you wish, thin soup with milk or water.
Season to taste.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream
sugar,
shortening and egg.
Add grated zucchini and drained pineapple.	Stir in the dry ingredients; add nuts and raisins
last.
Drop
on
greased
cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° or until no imprint is left when pressed.

title: sausage casserole
directions: In 3-quart casserole dish, layer bread, cheese and sausage. Repeat.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour over casserole. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Remove from refrigerate at least 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hash brown potato bake
directions: Place frozen potatoes in 1 1/2-quart microproof casserole dish. Cover; cook on High 5 minutes.
Stir in soup, sour cream, onions, salt, pepper and parsley.
Cover; cook on Medium for 12 minutes, stirring once during cooking time.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving.
tags: frozen southern style hash brown potatoes

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Cooked rice is added to cooked broccoli.
Add 1 can chicken soup and 16 ounce jar Cheez Whiz with a little chopped onion and 1/2 cup milk to broccoli-rice mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: amish sugar cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add milk and cook until thick. When thick, add butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into partially baked pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until it starts to bubble.

title: cinnamon tea
directions: Combine cinnamon sticks and water in large saucepan.
Boil for 3 minutes; remove from heat.
Add tea bags.
Let steep for 10 minutes; remove cinnamon sticks and tea bags.
Stir in sugar. Heat just to serving temperature.
Serve in cups with cinnamon sticks for stirrers.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in butter until tender. Heat mushroom soup and cheese over low heat until cheese is melted.
Add broccoli and the sauteed mixture.
Blend well. Serve warm with tostados.
Makes about 1 quart.
May be frozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Mix all ingredients except broccoli and stuffing mix.
Salt to taste. Stir in broccoli.
Put in a buttered casserole dish.
Top with herb stuffing.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all and pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Top with crushed cornflakes mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugars, pumpkin, oil and eggs; beat until well blended. Sift flour, soda, salt and spices together.
Stir into pumpkin mixture.
Stir in nuts and water; spoon into well oiled 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until bread tests done.
Turn out on rack to cool.

title: ice cream watermelon dessert
directions: You will need one plastic lettuce crisper or other oval shaped mold.
Spread lime sherbet along the sides of the lettuce crisper, making a layer about 1 inch to 1 1/2 inches thick along all sides and leaving a cavity in the center (this is the rind of watermelon).
Kids will enjoy smooshing the ice cream around. Fill the center cavity with strawberry or raspberry ice cream, adding chocolate chips (the seeds) as you go along.
Chill in freezer for at least 6 hours.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Cook, peel and chop potatoes.
Combine first 7 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Arrange on salad greens when ready to serve.

title: crescent dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and add a pinch of sugar to feed the yeast.
Melt the shortening in the milk; add sugar and stir to dissolve.
Cool.
Stir in and knead in as necessary the flour and salt mixture.
Refrigerate overnight covered.

title: better 'n cobbler
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Mix remaining ingredients together and put in greased baking dish.
Put cherry mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Place ham ends or bone and water in Dutch oven.
Boil until tender.
Remove ham and cut into pieces.
Put diced potatoes, onion, celery and seasonings into the stock.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add ham back to broth.

title: oatmeal toffee cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Lightly grease cookie sheet. Beat butter, eggs, brown sugar and vanilla until well blended. Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; beat until blended. Stir in oats, toffee bits, and coconut, if desired. Drop dough by rounded teaspoons about 2 inches apart onto prepared cookie sheet. Bake 8 - 10 minutes or until edges are lightly browned. Cool 1 minute, then remove to wire rack. Yield: 4 dozen.

title: easy seafood salad
directions: Mix everything together in large bowl.
Ready to serve.

title: ladies luncheon chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles; seal perforations.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture onto center of each rectangle; pull 4 corners of dough to the center and seal top and sides.
Brush tops with 1 tablespoon butter, melted.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: spicy pear cobbler
directions: Combine sugar and nutmeg (save about 1/4 of mixture).
Blend in saucepan, 3/4 of mixture and cornstarch.
Stir in juice and coloring.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly. Add pears and butter.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and syrup, then salt and vanilla last. Add melted butter.
Place pecans in bottom of pie crust.
Add the filling.
Bake slowly in oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: north pole reindeer food(aka granola)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, except fruits, together in a large bowl.
In small saucepan, bring oil and honey to boil.
Add to dry mixture and mix well.
Spread in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and add fruits (raisins, currants, dates, apricots, etc.).
Store immediately in airtight container.

title: truly different cupcakes
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate.
Add butter flavoring and nuts. Mix flour, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Combine the two mixes with a spoon.
Fill cupcake tins 2/3 full.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°. Do not overbake as the tops should be soft, making the cupcakes "self-frosted."
These freeze well.
Yield:
18 cupcakes.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
In a large bowl mix flour, sugar, pecans, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Combine eggs, bananas, oil, vanilla and pineapple in medium bowl. Stir, by hand,

into flour mixture until flour is just moistened. Grease two 9 x 5 inch loaf pans. Turn batter into pans. Check with tooth pick. Cool pan for 10 minutes before removing from pan. I use small pans, makes 5 or 6 loaves.

title: tasty dump cake
directions: In greased baking pan, blend flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and baking soda together.
Add vanilla and vinegar.
Pour 2 cups of water over mixture and blend until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Bring applesauce to a boil.
Add both packs of Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Add orange juice.
Stir.
Refrigerate to gel.

title: pig lickin cake
directions: Mix together. Bake in 2 layers at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy apricot nectar cake
directions: Beat ingredients on medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into a well greased 9 by 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: dublin stew and dumplings
directions: Brown pork in butter in 4-quart Dutch oven. Add onion, celery, garlic and salt.
Brown lightly. Dissolve bouillon cubes in water. Blend into meat mixture.
Add carrots.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Combine 1/4 cup flour with 1/2 cup water to form a smooth paste. Add slowly to meat mixture. Stir carefully until thickened.
Add mixed vegetables. Top with dumplings.
Cover tightly and steam 25 minutes.

title: sugar-free lemon pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in small bowl to dissolve. Combine rest of ingredients in bowl; beat.
Add gelatin mixture; beat until smooth.
Turn into shell.
Chill overnight.
If desired, can put Cool Whip on top when served.

title: barley and mushroom casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms in half of the butter.
Remove mushrooms from skillet and season with salt, pepper and marjoram.
Brown barley and chopped onions in remaining butter.
Add mushrooms to the barley and chopped onion mixture and put into a buttered casserole.
Cover with chicken broth and bake covered for 2 hours at 300°.
Add more chicken broth during baking, as needed.
Adjust seasoning, as needed.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mushroom steak
directions: Cut steak into 4-inch pieces.
Melt butter or margarine in large pot with Worcestershire.
Sear meat on high heat until light brown on each side.
Turn down to simmer.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover and simmer for 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until tender.
Stir frequently.
Serve over noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: carrots marinade
directions: Cut carrots in julienne strips.
Cook in small amount of water until barely tender; drain and cook.
Slice onion thinly and cut pepper into strips.
Combine with carrots.
Mix the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over carrots, onions and pepper, chill.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain. Arrange in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken over broccoli.
Salt and pepper.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over chicken.
Put bread crumb mixture over top and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: secret kisses
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla until creamy; add flour and nuts.
Chill dough.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix together the yeast and hot water.
Stir in salt, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Add vegetable oil.
Spoon into 12-hole greased muffin pans 3/4 full.
Let raise.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour dressing just prior to serving.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken cutlets in bottom of casserole pan.
Put Swiss cheese over top of cutlets.
Combine cream of mushroom soup with mushrooms and pour on top of cheese cutlets.
Pour package of bread cubes from Stove Top over entire dish.
Sprinkle about 1/2 of Stove Top seasoning over dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with egg noodles (cook according to package) and fresh French bread.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir in stuffing.
Line casserole with 1/2 mixture.
Mix other ingredients and spoon on top.
Cover with rest of stuffing.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken in chunks.
Sprinkle generously with seasoning and cover with buttermilk.
Cover dish and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Dredge in self-rising flour and deep fry.
Also good for steak fingers.

title: cold pack dill pickles
directions: Fill jars with cold water and seal.
Put jars in canner and bring to a boiling point.

title: chocolate chip and nut cookies
directions: Refrigerate batter for 1 hour.
Scoop with ice cream scoop to make each cookie uniform, and place on sprayed greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until lightly browned on top. Do not let batter get warm between baking, or cookies will spread out too far on cookie sheet and will not be uniform.

title: swedish pie
directions: Beat sugar, egg and vanilla until fluffy.
In another bowl, combine walnuts, flour, salt, apples and baking powder.
Combine both mixtures.
Grease a 9-inch pie pan.
Pour batter in.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: * I use American and Monterey Jack.

title: italian salad
directions: Mix lettuce, tomatoes, cucumber, pepper, onion, olives, croutons, cheeses and seasonings.
Pour Italian salad dressing over mixture; mix well.
Serve immediately.

title: coconut pie with self-made crust
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in pie pan for one hour at 325°.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and prick several times with a fork.
Place in a food Baggie leaving open at the end.
Bake in microwave 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Prick with fork to check for doneness.

title: rice and sour cream casserole
directions: Grate cheese; chop chilies and mix all together.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle paprika or parsley on top.

title: crunchy cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let cool.
Add other ingredients.
Put into mold that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Unmold onto lettuce.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together mushroom soup, eggs, mayonnaise, cheese and onion and put in bowl with broccoli.
Mix together crackers and oleo and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion until brown, drain and add the rest of the ingredients.
Heat until hot.

title: easy breakfast dish
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put into a well-greased 9 x 13 pan. Refrigerate 12 hours. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: uncooked relish
directions: Put each vegetable through food chopper, using coarse blade. If vegetables are covered with liquid, drain off and discard liquid.
Measure each vegetable after chopping.
Mix vegetables with salt and let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain off and discard all liquid.
Add spices, sugar and vinegar to drained vegetables and mix well.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal at once.
This relish is very good on hot dogs or hamburgers.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Melt Hershey bars.
Melt peanut butter bars.
Melt more Hershey chocolate bars.
Cut down cupcake liners to 1-inch deep and place in cupcake pan.
Use equal amounts of both Hershey chocolate bars and peanut butter bars. Let each layer set for 1/2 hour.

title: italian beef
directions: Mix 4 cups of water and all seasonings in a roaster pan. Place roast in pan and bake in oven at 325° for 3 to 4 hours. Baste roast occasionally; cut string the last 1/2 hour of cooking and baste well with juices.
Put roast and juices in a crock-pot and cook until the meat falls apart in strings.
Serve on French, Italian bread or hot rolls.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter and cool.
Add all other ingredients one at a time.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and cook for 40 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: chili sauce
directions: Boil together until thick.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese; add pineapple, onion, bell peppers and shredded cheese.
Roll into a ball and cover with finely chopped nuts.
Chill.

title: shredded beef
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a bowl. Add any dressing that you like. You may serve it on large pieces of Mexican tortilla chips.

title: tangerine dressing
directions: Combine thyme, salt and pepper in a quick shake container or small bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: pancakes
directions: Use any pancake mix.
Add extra cup of milk to make pancakes extra thin.
Cook as directed.
Place on plate and spread with a generous portion of sour cream.
Put another pancake on top and cover with strawberry sauce.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage; steam until tender and drain.
Place in 9 x 13 inch baking dish crush 20 crackers and toss with cabbage.
Cube cheese and toss over cabbage.
In saucepan melt 1 stick margarine and stir in flour.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Season with salt, pour over cabbage mixture.
Prepare topping by melting 1 stick margarine, remaining crackers, crushed, and mix together. Spread over cabbage.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour until golden brown and bubbly.
Makes 12-15 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, vanilla and salt; add flour and soda. Mix well, then add chips and nuts. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut up chicken and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Heat broth, soup, margarine and mixed vegetables until margarine melts. Pour over chicken.
Place pie crust on top.
Bake in 450° oven for about thirty minutes or until golden brown.

title: 30 minute yeast bread(124 servings)
directions: Combine water, oil, sugar and yeast.
Let rest 15 minutes.
Add salt and eggs and mix well.
Stir in flour.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth.
Shape immediately into rolls, buns, pizza crust or other desired products.
Let rise for 10 minutes. Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until browned.

title: salmon steaks
directions: Heat oven to 350° and place steaks on ungreased baking pan. Squeeze fresh lemon juice onto steaks and sprinkle with desired amount of dill.
Bake salmon for 17 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Garnish with lemon slices, if desired.

title: potato-oatmeal bread
directions: Boil potato in water; drain and place cooked potato in large mixing bowl.
Cool potato water to 105°; ice may be used to achieve this temperature.
Add yeast and sugar to 1 1/2 cups potato water and set aside to activate (takes about 10 minutes). Add buttermilk to potato and blend.
Add oil, molasses, sugar and salt to potato mixture and blend.
Add activated yeast mixture and blend.
Add oatmeal and blend.
Add flour until dough forms a soft, but not sticky, ball that can be kneaded.

title: holly's blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
In a separate bowl mix egg, milk and oil.
Add to flour and mix by hand.
Cover blueberries with flour and add to the batter.
Spray muffin pans with Pam. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Brush tops with butter.
Sprinkle with sugar before and after baking.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix flour, soda and sugar together.
Cut in shortening as for pastry.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk and mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Place in covered container and chill well.
Use as needed.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, milk and chocolate over low heat.
Stir until boil soft ball stage.
Add salt, oleo and vanilla.
Cool, then beat until thick and creamy; pour in buttered pan.

title: easy chicken pasties
directions: Let dough thaw until pliable.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Cut loaf of bread dough crosswise into 8 slices. Using a little flour on board and rolling pin; pat and roll dough pieces out to 5-inch diameter circles.
Place filling in lengthwise strip down centers of dough circles.
Pull dough edges up and pinch together to form a ridge across top of pastry.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook chicken in just enough water to cover 20 to 30 minutes. Remove chicken to cool and add soup to broth creaming as you add. Add water, onion and green chilies.
Cut up cooled chicken and add to soup mixture.
Put mixture on low fire to warm.
Grate cheese and mix together.
Tear tortillas in chips and fry in oil.

title: banana nut bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well; pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Seems better if frozen awhile. Mmmm good.

title: cheese sandwich spread
directions: Blend cream cheese until smooth.
Add other ingredients.
Blend well.
May need to add salad dressing to permit spreading. Refrigerate.

title: marinated carrot sticks
directions: Combine vinegar, garlic, parsley, salad oil and salt.
Pour over carrot sticks and marinate overnight.
If placed in Tupperware bowl, bowl can be turned over to keep carrots coated with marinade.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg yolks. Dredge fruit with flour and add to mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff and add to mixture. Mix well. Pour in tube pan. Bake at 275° for 2 hours. Cool in pan.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1 stick of oleo; set aside.
Cream sugar and 1 stick of oleo.
Add eggs, then flour, alternating with buttermilk that soda has been stirred in.
Add candy and oleo mixture, pecans, coconut and vanilla.
Bake in Bundt pan until done at 325°.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix ingredients well and bake in hot greased muffin pan at 425° until golden brown. Yields 20 to 24 rolls.

title: praline topping
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and butter.
Heat to boiling point.
Remove from stove and cool.
When mixture is lukewarm, add Pet milk. Store in refrigerator.
Top with chopped pecans when ready to serve or mix into mixture when cooled.
Praline topping may be served on ice cream or cheesecake.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar, nutmeg, lemon juice and salt.
Add cold cream and milk.
Beat with eggbeater.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix hot water and oats; let stand.
Cream white and brown sugars and shortening.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Set sugar and egg mixture aside.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add dry mixture alternately with oatmeal mixture to sugar and egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean at center of cake in 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: easy graham cracker pudding #3
directions: Bring milk, graham cracker crumbs, eggs and sugar to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cool thoroughly (I prefer overnight).
Beat cold pudding with electric mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Sprinkle a few cracker crumbs on top.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Blend all ingredients (except crab) until well mixed.
Add crabmeat.
Heat in double boiler.
Serve warm.

title: grandma's hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Add milk and butter.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.
Serve warm over ice cream.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: mayonnaise chocolate cake
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients; beat with mixer.
Batter will be thin.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 layer pans at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: hamburger jumble(microwave)
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Pour in casserole dish and layer the rest.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Cream the cheese and margarine using electric mixer.
Slowly blend in flour; stir in Rice Krispies and cayenne pepper.
Drop batter by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork to make round wafers.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Store in an airtight container to keep crisp.

title: fried macaroni
directions: In a large skillet, place butter, garlic powder and onion flakes.
When butter is melted, add cooked macaroni.
Allow macaroni to fry on low 20 minutes, until crispy and golden. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Simmer until it melts.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Bake cake in flat cookie sheet pan.
Mix pudding and cream cheese together.
Cool cake.
Layer pudding mixture over top of cake.
Drain pineapple well, and layer over pudding.
Layer Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with coconut and nuts.

title: chicken and cheese casserole
directions: Boil egg noodles.
Crumble up chicken; add the cream of chicken soup and heat.
Pour in noodles.
Stir it up.
Add cheese and bake approximately 1 hour.

title: louisiana barbecued beans
directions: Fry bacon in a 4 to 6-quart capacity pot until crisp.
Add onions and saute until clear.
Add beans and stir.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Stir well and lower heat to simmer.
Let simmer, uncovered, until cooked down to consistency desired (about 2 hours or more).

title: earthquake cake
directions: Into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, put coconut and pecans.
Mix cake mix according to directions and pour on top of pecans and coconut.
In separate bowl, mix together cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Spoon on top of cake mix.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven as cake bakes, the top cracks like an earthquake cracks the earth.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix the wafer crumbs, butter and nuts.
Put half of the mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cut the ice cream into slices and place over crumbs.
Top with balance of crumb mixture. Put in freezer until serving time.
Cut into squares and serve with Chocolate Sauce.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Pat ground meat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer noodles on top. Pour sauces on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven to melt cheese.

title: tuna cream cheese spread
directions: Heat soup.
Add gelatin; cool.
Beat in cream cheese until smooth, then add remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Drain salmon and discard skin and bones.
Flake with fork. Mix together stuffing mix with 3/4 c water, mayonnaise, cheese, onions and
fish.
Mix well, cover and refrigerate for 10 minutes. Heat large non-stick skillet sprayed with Pam on medium heat. Shape 1/3 c of mixture into patties; add to skillet being careful not
to over crowd patties.
Cook 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown on both sides, turning carefully.
Makes 6 servings of 2 patties each.

title: rocky mountain cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add egg whites 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix flour and baking powder in bowl; mix well.
Add to egg white mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in almond extract.
Pour into 4 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cakes test done.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Spread frosting between layers and over top and side of cake.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: acadian poutines
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll dough thinly.
Cut into strips, then snip into any kind of stew.
Allow 15 minutes cooking time.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Select well-shaped mushrooms with closed caps.
Wash quickly under water and drain on paper towels. Pull stems from mushrooms and finely chop.

title: shrimp pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until tender; drain and rinse under cold water in colander.
Steam vegetables; add to pasta.
Add dill and salad dressing to shrimp.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix meat, onion, celery, garlic powder and salt.
Make up balls and brown at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add meatballs to sauce.

title: chicken meal soup
directions: Boil chicken, onions, celery and spices in 2 quarts water. When chicken is done, remove from stock; save.
Debone chicken; put back in pot.
On low heat, stir corn meal in the liquid, 1/2 cup at a time, until you get the thickness you want.
Real good when sick!

title: magic bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter. Sprinkle crumbs over butter; pour milk over the crumbs.
Top evenly with chocolate chips, coconut and pecans.
Press down gently.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: 1 step macaroni and cheese
